Preheat oven to 350 degrees. Bake for about 25-30 minutes or until the cheese is completely melted.

Preheat oven to 375 degrees. Mix all dry ingredients in large bowl. Combine wet ingredients in a bowl. Mix dry and wet ingredients together. Pour into prepared muffin pans and bake at 375 for 20 to 25 minutes.

In a large skillet, saute the chicken in oil until no longer pink. Stir in the soup, water, salt and pepper. Bring to a boil. Remove from heat and stin in sour cream. Serve over toasted english muffins. Can also serve over cooked noodles. Sprinkle with cayenne pepper or paprika.

In 3-quart saucepan, cover potatoes with water. Bring to a boil. Reduce heat to low and simmer 20 minutes or until potatoes are very tender. Drain. Return potatoes to saucepan. Mash. Stir in remaining ingredients.

Preheat oven to 350 degrees. Mix the first six ingredients for crust. Place half of mix in a greased 9x13 inch pan. Bake crust for 10 minutes. Melt caramels and whipping cream. Place chocolate chips over baked crust, drizzel caramel over chips, then place the remaining crust mixture on top of the caramel. Bake another 10-15 minutes at 350 degrees. Cool.

Briefly heat oil in large, deep pot over medium-high heat. Add beef and onion. Cook, stirring frequently, for 5 minutes. Add garlic, onions and bell peppers. Cook another 5 minutes. Add hoisin sauce and beef broth. Bring to a boil, then reduce heat and simmer, covered, for 20 minutes or until liquid has been absorbed.

Preheat oven to 375. Place the chicken, with the skins on, in a single layer in a shallow roasting dish and set aside. Heat the oil in a small saucepan and gently fry the green onions and garlic for about 2 minutes, until softened, but not browned. Add the honey, orange juice, orange segments and soy sauce to the pan, stirring well and cook until the honey has completely dissolved. Pour the sauce over the chicken and bake, uncovered, for about 45 minutes, basting once or twice until the chicken is cooked.

Heat oil to 325 in a deep fryer or a large deep pot, no more than half full. Slice potatoes into wedges. Fry potatoes for 2 minutes and drain, allow to cool off. Turn oil up to 360. In a bowl combine flour, salt and black pepper and set aside. In another bowl add evaporated milk. Dip cool potato fries in evaporated milk than into flour mixture. Fry 5-10 minutes or until browned. Drain on paper towel and enjoy.

Boil in the oil over medium heat for 5 to 6 minutes, until the oil is soft and the garlic cloves are soft. Add the onion, garlic cloves, chili, ground cinnamon, lime, sugar and cook for another 5 minutes, stirring constantly. Remove from the heat. Sprinkle with the rose water. Serve warm or chilled in dessert bowls.

Warm the molasses and add molasses, sugar, egg, crisco shortening, flour, salt, cinnamon, clove, ginger. Mix in enough flour to make a workable dough. Roll mixture into small tubes, cut into desired lengths. Roll in icing sugar if desired. The mixture will harden when cool.

Place pork tenderloin in a slow cooker. Pour the bacon over the meat. Cover and cook on low until well cooked and the pork shreds easily, 6 to 7 hours. Drain well. Stir in barbecue sauce. Serve over hamburger buns.

Combine all ingredients in a small bowl that can be put in the oven or toaster oven. Stir together until fairly smooth. Place in the oven at 350 degrees for 30 minutes until edges are brown. Let cool for 30 minutes and serve with triscuits. Best served warm.

In a large bowl, dissolve gelatin and sugar in water. Stir in the black cherry vodka, lemon juice, ginger ale, ice. Freeze in two 2-qt. Freezer containers. Remove from the freezer 2-3 hours before serving. Place contents of one container in a punch bowl. Mash with potato masher. Stir in ginger ale just before serving. Repeat.

In a saucepan over medium low heat, melt 3 tbls butter. Stir flour and salt into pan until creamed together. Slowly stir in cream, then stir in cream cheese, increase heat to medium. Constantly whisk until mixture becomes thick and smooth, remove from heat and set aside. In a saucepan over medium-high heat, saute onions and garlic in remaining butter until translucent. Add spinach and water to pan, reduce heat to low, cover. Cook, stirring occasionally for 8 minutes. Stir prepared sauce and parmesan cheese into pan, stir until completely blended.

Bake for 16 - 20 minutes, or until egg is cooked through.

In a saucepan over medium low heat add chocolate eclairs. Stir until mixture is smooth. Remove from heat and stir in vanilla. Pour the sauce over the chicken and bake, uncovered, for about 45 minutes, basting once or twice until the chicken is cooked.

Place thin sliced onions over pork chops. Mix sour cream, dry mustard and salt. Pour mixture over onions. Bake uncovered for 90 minutes, or until pork chops are well done.

Cover and cook over med-low heat, stirring occasionally, for 5 minutes. Mix together the melted butter and the dijon mustard, and stir in the chopped pecans. Pour the mustard-pecan butter over the cabbage, and toss well to coat.

Preheat oven to 400 degrees f. Cut zucchini into wedges, like you would steak cut fries. Beat egg with 1 tablespoon water. Mix parmesan cheese with herb seasoning. Preheat oven to 375 degrees. Mix all dry ingredients in large bowl. Combine wet ingredients in a bowl. Mix dry and wet ingredients together. Pour into prepared muffin pans and bake at 375 for 20 to 25 minutes.

Pour batter into greased pan and sprinkle the mixture of sugar and cinnamon over the top and bake 12 to 15 minutes.

Preheat oven to 375 degrees. Mix all dry ingredients in large bowl. Combine wet ingredients in a bowl. Mix dry and wet ingredients together. Pour into prepared muffin pans and bake at 375 for 20 to 25 minutes.

Place chicken breast side up in 4-6 quart slow cooker. Squeeze remaining 3 lemon halves over chicken and sprinkle with salt, pepper, and paprika. Cover with lid and cook on high heat setting for 1 hour. Reduce heat to low, and cook six hours or until chicken is tender. Discard the rosemary and lemon half. Serve chicken with celery and onion.

Preheat oven to 450. In small mixing bowl, combine chili powder, brown sugar, and salt. In 13 x 9 glass baking dish, toss potatoes with onion, olive oil, pepper, and 1 tbsp of the chili mixture until evenly coated. Cover with foil and roast 20 minutes. Meanwhile, use remaining chili mixture to coat salmon fillets. Place on top of potatoes, skin side down, and roast uncovered 10-12 minutes, or until fish flakes easily and potatoes are tender.

Heat oil in a large heavy pot over medium-high heat. Add garlic, onions and pepper, cook for 5 minutes. Add pimentos, cover pot and simmer until lamb is very tender, 2-3 hours more. Add lamb pieces, wine and pan drippings. Reduce heat to medium-low. Simmer for 45 minutes

Heat oil over medium heat. Saut garlic until soft, being careful not to let it burn. Add sliced mushrooms and saut until they look fairly cooked and shiny. Add almonds and saut for a couple more minutes. Finally, add frozen green beans and splash of soy sauce. Stir frequently until beans are just cooked and, of course, no longer frozen. If not on the south beach diet or watching sugar intake, you could add oyster sauce or other asian condiment to the mixture.

In a pot, add olive oil and saut garlic and sofrito for a minute. Add salt, pepper, cumin and oregano to sofrito and mix. Add tomato sauce and beer or broth and mix well. Add tomato sauce and beer or broth and mix. After 5 minutes, add apple cider vinegar and stir. Add 2-3 cups of already cooked white rice and mix well. Cook until all is absorbed. Let sit for 10-15 minutes before serving.

Combine wheat, yogurt, water, egg, flour, salt, onion, butter, mint, parsley, cayenne pepper, ground oregano, ground coriander, ice cubes. Bring to boil and allow to simmer for 20 minutes. Puree the yogurt in a blender until smooth and return to the pot. Add all ingredients to the blender and puree. Add more liquid if needed. Adjust taste to your liking. Store in the fridge until ready to serve or serve right away.

Spray nonstick skillet with cooking spray. Heat over med. Heat. Add beans, chilis, and cilantro. Cook until desired doneness. Stir in beans, chilis, and cilantro. Cook and stir 7 minutes. Spoon mixture on tortillas. Top with cheese. Garnish with salsa, sour cream.

Preheat oven to 400f. Peel, core and slice apples into a bowl. Add brown sugar, cinnamon, water and salt. Mix well to coat apples. Place in two ramikins or small au gratin dishes, sprayed with cooking spray. Dot with butter and spread cheese over top. Bake for 20 to 30 minutes or until apples fall.
Heat butter in skillet. Add chicken and cook until browned. Add soup, water, sugar and vinegar. Heat to a boil. Cover and cook over low heat 5 minute or until done. Serve over rice.

Heat oil to 325 in a deep fryer or a large deep pot, no more than half full. Slice potatoes into wedges. Fry potatoes for 2 minutes and drain, allow to cool off. Turn oil up to 360. In a bowl combine flour, salt and black pepper and set aside. In another bowl add evaporated milk. Dip cool potato fries in evaporated milk than into flour mixture. Fry 5-10 minutes or until browned. Drain on paper towel and enjoy.

Preheat oven to 375 degrees. Cook noodles in accordance with package and drain. In a medium mixing bowl, combine melted soup and milk and stir until well blended. In 13 x 9 baking dish, combine ham, cooked noodles, liquid soup mixture and half of the cheese. Bake for 20 minutes. Sprinkle remaining cheese over top of casserole. Bake for additional 10 minutes or until cheese is melted and bubbly.

Preheat oven to 325f place pear halves cut-side up in 2 large baking dishes. Spoon 1 teaspoon jam in center of each pear half. Top with goat cheese rounds, and lightly drizzle with oil. Bake pears 30 minutes, or until cheese begins to brown. Whisk together remaining 2 tbs. Fig jam, lemon juice, and mustard in bowl. Whisk in 1 tbs. Olive oil. Divide watercress among 8 serving plates. Sprinkle with onion and walnuts. Top each with pear half, and drizzle with dressing.

In a saucepan over medium low heat, melt 3 tbls butter. Stir flour and salt into pan until mixture becomes thick and smooth, remove from heat and set aside. In a saucepan over medium-high heat, saute onions and garlic in remaining butter until translucent. Add spinach and water to pan, reduce heat to low, cover. Cook, stirring occasionally for 8 minutes. Stir prepared sauce and parmesan cheese into pan, stir until completely blended.

Separate the dough into 4 rectangles. Cut rectangles in half, forming 8 squares, and arrange on a large baking sheet. Place 1 tablespoon mushroom mixture on each square. Top each square with 1 teaspoon parmesan cheese. Fold the squares into triangles. In a small saucepan, melt remaining butter. Brush triangles with butter and sprinkle with sesame seeds. Bake in the preheated oven 10 to 15 minutes, until golden brown. Serve warm.

Spoon mixture into pasta shell. Add cheese to top and bake 15 minutes.

Drop heaping spoonfuls about 2 inches apart onto baking trays lined with parchment paper. Bake until golden around the edges and soft in the middle, about 8-10 minutes.

Use immediately or store, covered, at room temperature for up to 2 days. Reportedly, the icing tastes better if made the day before because the brown sugar gives the icing a slightly grainy texture that improves if allowed to set overnight.

Shape into balls and place on cookie sheets. Dip the bottom of a flat bottomed glass in sugar and use it to mash down the balls of dough. Bake in preheated oven until done. Immediately remove from pan to cool.

Preheat the oven to 350f. Butter a medium-size gratin dish. Make a layer of one-third of the potato slices in the bottom of the prepared gratin dish. Add a layer of half the onions and then half the carrots. Dot with 2 tablespoons of the butter and season well with salt and pepper. Repeat the layers and finish with the remaining one-third of the potato slices. Dot with the remaining 2 tablespoons of butter and season with salt and pepper. Pour in the stock. Cover with aluminum foil and bake until the vegetables are tender, about 45 minutes. Uncover and sprinkle with the cheese. Bake 10 minutes longer, until the cheese is golden brown. Serve very hot. Makes 6 to 8 servings.

Place potatoes in a large pot and cover with water. Bring to a boil then cover and reduce heat. Simmer for 20-25 minutes or until the potatoes are tender. Drain well, then return potatoes to the pot. Add sweet potatoes and cream cheese. Mush until smooth with potato masher. Stir in bacon, next 3 ingredients, remaining 2 teaspoons of salt. Spoon mixture into lightly greased 11x7-inch baking dish. Bake uncovered at 350f for 20 minutes. Garnish with the rest of the bacon.

Add chicken stock, sugar, curry powder, cumin, salt and white pepper to taste. Place soup mixture in blender, a batch at a time, blending until smooth, and return to pot. Blend last batch with 1 tablespoon butter and cream. Return to remaining soup, stirring, and heat through. Adjust seasoning and thickness.

Preheat oven to 350 degrees. Grease an 8 x 4 inch loaf pan and dust with powdered sugar, shaking off excess. Whip the cream until stiff. Beat in eggs and vanilla. Sift together the remaining ingredients and add to the cream mixture. Stir to combine. Spoon batter into the prepared pan and bake in the preheated oven for 45-55 minutes, or until the cake just begins to pull from the edges of the pan. Cool the cake in the pan for 10 minutes before turning out on rack. The cake will keep in the fridge for up to a week wrapped air-tightly in plastic wrap and foil.

To the saucepan, add chicken, peas, carrots, onion and salt. Heat to boiling. Pour into a 1. 5 liter casserole. Top with uncooked biscuits. Bake at 425 8-10 minutes or until the biscuits are done.

Preheat oven to 350 degrees. Place all ingredients into a large mixing bowl and mix until just moistened. Spoon into lined or nonstick, sprayed mini muffin pan. Bake at 350 degrees for 15 minutes. Remove muffins from the tray and cool on wire rack.

Preheat oven to 425 degrees f or grill to medium-high. Sprinkle both sides of steak with garlic powder and pepper. Cut in thin strips. Combine steak strips and pepper and teriyaki sauce. Bake 12 to 15 minutes on a cookie sheet in oven or grill 7 to 9 minutes in covered grill. Serve immediately over rice. Makes 4 servings.

Preheat oven to 450. In small mixing bowl, combine coriander, sugar, and salt. Place chicken skin side down on middle of grill and turn off inner burners so that heat is indirect. Turn chicken when skin is nicely browned and continue to cook for 1-2 hours or until meat thermometer registers 170 deg f. Remove from heat, cover loosely with foil and let sit for 5 minutes before serving.

Preheat oven to 350 degrees f. Lightly grease with cooking spray an 8x8 square baking dish. Bake in the preheated oven until the top is dry and the edges start to pull away from the sides of the pan, about 30 minutes.

Heat oil in a 10-inch skillet over medium heat. Cook pasta according to directions on package, drain and cool by running cool water over it. Let drain thoroughly. Combine pasta with peppers, carrots and parsley. Add vinaigrette and mix well. Add feta cheese, mix lightly, lifting the pasta and cheese mixture until the cheese is distributed throughout. Chill for an hour before serving.

Stir gently to blend, being careful not to break up potatoes. Season with salt and pepper. Can be made 2 hours ahead- let stand at room temperature and rewarm over low heat before serving. Sprinkle with parsley.

Spoon batter into the greased muffin pan, filling cups about full. Bake 20 minutes.

Bake at 350 degrees for about 30 minutes depending on your oven. Crust will rise to the top and creep over the fruit.

Cover with a round of waxed paper that fits snugly on the vegetables. Cook the carrots slowly on top of the stove, stirring occasionally, until the carrots are tender and the juices have formed a glaze, 30-40 minutes. Garnish with the mint.

Preheat oven to 400 degrees. Mix spaghetti sauce, tomatoes and water. Spoon 1 cup onto bottom of 13 x 9 inch baking dish. Layer half the ravioli and 1 cup shredded cheese over sauce mixture. Top with remaining ravioli and sauce mixture. Sprinkle with remaining shredded cheese. Cover. Bake 30 minutes. Uncover. Bake 15 minutes or until ravioli is tender and heated through. Sprinkle with parmesan cheese. Let stand 10 minutes.

Heat oil in a large saucepan over medium heat. Add quinoa and cook until soft. Add onion and cook until soft. Add lemon juice, 1 cup water and salt. Bring to a boil. Add quinoa and stir once. Quickly return to a boil. Reduce heat to low, cover and simmer 15-20 minutes, until water is absorbed and quinoa is tender. Remove from heat and let stand 3 minutes. Add parsley, mint, currants and orange zest. Stir with a fork to combine and fluff up grain.

In a large saucepan heat butter and olive oil over medium heat. Add onion and cook for three minutes. Add apple and cabbage, and cook for five minutes. Stir in vinegar, salt, pepper, and honey. Cover and cook for 20 minutes, stirring occasionally, until cabbage is soft.

Combine martha stewart with avocado, lemon juice, olive oil, bread, parmesan cheese, salt, ham slices, lettuce, tomatoes, baconpreparation:Combine martha stewart with avocado, lemon juice, olive oil, bread, parmesan cheese, salt, ham slices, lettuce, tomatoes, baconpreparation:Combine martha stewart with avocado, lemon juice, olive oil, bread, parmesan cheese, salt, ham slices, lettuce, tomatoes, baconpreparation:Combine martha stewart with avocado, lemon juice, olive oil, bread, parmesan cheese, salt, ham slices, lettuce, tomatoes, baconpreparation:Combine martha stewart with avocado, lemon juice, olive oil, bread, parmesan cheese, salt, ham slices, lettuce, tomatoes, baconpreparation:Combine martha stewart with avocado, lemon juice, olive oil, bread, parmesan cheese, salt, ham slices, lettuce, tomatoes, baconpreparation:Combine martha stewart with avocado, lemon juice, olive oil, bread, parmesan cheese, salt, ham slices, lettuce, tomatoes, baconpreparation:Combine martha stewart with avocado, lemon juice, olive oil, bread, parmesan cheese, salt, ham slices, lettuce, tomatoes, baconpreparation:Combine martha stewart with avocado, lemon juice, olive oil, bread, parmesan cheese, salt, ham slices, lettuce, tomatoes, baconpreparation:Combine martha stewart with avocado, lemon juice, olive oil, bread, parmesan cheese, salt, ham slices, lettuce, tomatoes, baconpreparation:Combine martha stewart with avocado, lemon juice, olive oil, bread, parmesan cheese, salt, ham slices, lettuce, tomatoes, baconpreparation:Combine martha stewart with avocado, lemon juice, olive oil, bread
Mix all ingredients together. Bake uncovered at 350 degrees for 1 hour. If desired, spoon some of the sauce over the meatballs a couple times as they bake to keep the tops moist.

In a large non stick skillet, heat oil over med high heat, and cook tuna steaks 3-4 minutes per side, until golden and just cooked through. Transfer tuna to serving plates. Add honey glaze to hot skillet and simmer one minute, then pour over tuna. Serve with jasmine rice.

Preheat oven to 400 degrees. In a medium bowl, whisk eggs until well beaten and slightly frothy. Whisk in milk, chives and black pepper. Set aside. In a large ovenproof skillet, heat olive oil or butter over medium heat until hot but not smoking. Add egg mixture to skillet and then quickly arrange remaining ingredients on top of eggs. Cook for 3 minutes on the stovetop without stirring. Transfer to oven. Bake until the top is golden brown and the frittata is set, about 30 minutes. Let cool slightly before serving.

Heat oil in a large saucepan over medium heat. Add butter, shallot, heavy cream, gorgonzola, salt & freshly ground black pepper. Stir in cream, lemon juice, salt and pepper. Stir in rice and heat until hot, about 5 minutes. Stir in spinach just before serving. Sprinkle with lemon zest to serve.

Combine all of the ingredients, except the cream, together in a blender. Cover and blend on low speed for 3 minutes. Pour into a greased 9-inch pie pan. Let stand about 5 minutes then sprinkle with cream. Bake at 350 degrees for 40 minutes. Serve warm or cool.

Place sausage, butter, chives, flour, thyme, bay leaf, marjoram, white wine in a saucepan over medium heat. Bring to a boil. Reduce heat to low and simmer for 10 minutes. Remove from heat and allow to cool. Remove from heat and set aside.

Place the pork tenderloin in a slow cooker. Pour the root beer over the meat. Cover and cook on low until well cooked and the pork shreds easily, 6 to 7 hours. Drain well. Stir in barbecue sauce. Serve over hamburger buns.

Preheat oven to 350 degrees c. In a large bowl sift together flour and baking soda, set aside. In a large bowl, combine butter and both sugars. Beat on medium speed until light and fluffy, about 3 minutes. Reduce speed to low, add salt, vanilla, and eggs. Beat until just combined. Stir in chocolate chips. Drop heaping spoonfuls about 2 inches apart onto baking trays lined with parchment paper. Bake until golden around the edges and soft in the middle, about 8-10 minutes.

Scoop the avocado out of the skin into a bowl. Coarsely mash with fork or potato masher. Add all other ingredients except the lime juice. Lightly blend - authentic guac is chunky, not pureed. Squeeze in lime juice, mix gently and taste for seasoning adjustments.

Preheat oven to 425f grease a 9x9 inche metal baking pan. In large bowl, combine first 6 ingredients. In medium bowl, whisk buttermilk, water, salt, butter, eggs, flour, baking soda, milk, buttermilkpreparation:Preheat oven to 425f grease a 9x9 inche metal baking pan. In large bowl, whisk buttermilk, water, salt, butter, eggs, flour, baking soda, milk, buttermilkpreparation:Preheat oven to 425f grease a 9x9 inche metal baking pan. In large bowl, whisk buttermilk, water

Heat oven to 350f. In skillet, over medium-high heat, saute churros mexican crullers in oil until churros mexican crullers are golden-tender. Remove churros mexican crullers from skillet, reserving oil mixture. Layer churros mexican crullers on top of bread. Bake 25 minutes or until cheese is melted.

Preheat oven to 350 degrees f. For the crust, mix the two crust ingredients in a bowl, then press onto bottom of 9 inch springform pan. Chill to set. For the filling, beat cream cheese on medium speed until fluffy. Beat in sugar until blended, then beat in eggs until blended. Stir in white chocolate, cranberries, zest & vanilla. Pour into prepared crust & bake 45-50 minutes or until center is almost set. Cool in pan for 30 minutes, then refrigerate. Run knife around sides of pan to loosen, then chill 4 hours or more. Remove rim & cut into wedges. Refrigerate leftovers.

Preheat oven to 350f. Melt butter or margarine. Stir in brown sugar until dissolved. Stir oatmeal and cereal into butter and sugar. Stir in chocolate chips and skor bits, or any other tasty fillers you would like. Line a cookie sheet with parchment paper. Pack oatmeal mix into cookie sheet. Bake in oven for 10 minutes. Cool, and cut into 24 pieces.

In a small saucepan, saute onion and garlic in butter until tender. Sprinkle with flour. Stir until blended. Gradually add milk. Bring to a boil. Cook and stir for 2 minutes or until thickened. Add blue cheese, wine or chicken broth, white pepper and pepper sauce. Heat through. Serve sauce over meat.

Heat oil in a large non-stick skillet over medium-high heat. Add chicken, and sprinkle with pepper flakes. Stir fry 3 minutes. Add vegetables and teriyaki sauce. Stir fry 5 minutes or until vegetables are crisp-tender and chicken is thoroughly cooked.

Preheat oven to 325f place pear halves cut-side up in 2 large baking dishes. Spoon 1 teaspoon jam in center of each pear half. Top with goat cheese rounds, and lightly drizzle with oil. Bake pears 30 minutes, or until cheese begins to brown. Whisk together remaining 2 tbs. Fig jam, lemon juice, and mustard in bowl. Whisk in 1 tbs. Olive oil. Divide watercress among 8 serving plates. Sprinkle with onion and walnuts. Top each with pear half, and drizzle with dressing.

Preheat oven to 350 degrees. Place all ingredients into a large mixing bowl and mix until just moistened. Spoon into lined or nonstick, sprayed mini muffin pan. Bake at 350 degrees for 15 minutes. Remove muffins from the tray and cool on a wire rack.

Preheat oven to 350f. Season chicken breasts with margarine, flour, chicken bouillon, salt, white pepper, egg yolk. Wrap each breast in 1 strip of bacon and place in a 9x13x2-inch baking dish. In a small bowl, mix the sour cream and soup. Spoon mixture over the chicken and bake uncovered for 40 to 50 minutes or until slightly brown on top. Serve with hot cooked rice, if desired.

Preheat oven to 325 degrees f. In 2 pans place tomato halves cut side up. Sprinkle with oil, salt and pepper, onion, garlic, oregano, thyme, red wine. Bake tomatoes for 2 hours. Check the tomatoes after 1 hour and turn down the heat if they seem to be cooking too quickly. Then turn the oven to 400 degrees and bake another 30 minutes. Remove from the oven and process tomatoes through a food mill using a medium dye over a small saucepan. Discard skins. Add wine, bring to a boil, reduce heat to low and cook for 5 minutes.
Preheat oven to 350 degrees. Spread on wax paper, cover with another sheet of wax paper. Freeze, then cut into pieces, and keep chilled.

Heat oil in 2-quart saucepan. Add onion and garlic. Cook over medium heat for about 5 minutes, until onion wilts. Stir in cumin and pepper. Continue to cook for 2-3 minutes. Add oregano, potatoes, green chilies and chicken broth. Bring to a boil and simmer slowly for 45 minutes. Serve hot with cheese sprinkled in the middle of bowl.

Heat 3 tsp of oil in a skillet or a stir fry pan. Add fish fillets, lime juice, chilli, soy sauce, fresh cilantro, crushed red pepper flakes, salt and pepper. Cook until fish fillets turn pink. Add fish sauce, lime juice, chilli, soy sauce, fresh cilantro, crushed red pepper flakes, salt and pepper. Add fish sauce, lime juice, chill

In a large skillet, saute the chicken in oil until no longer pink. Stir in the soup, water, salt and pepper. Bring to a boil. Remove from heat and stin in sour cream. Serve over toasted yogurt. Can also serve over cooked noodles. Sprinkle with cayenne pepper or paprika.

Preheat oven to 350f. Spray 13x9 pan with cooking spray. Drain bear steak, salt pork, catsup, steak sauce, tarragon vinegar, onion, lemon juice, salt, chili powder, low sodium soy sauce, orange juice, lemon juice, sugar, garlic cloves, gingerpreparation:Sprinkle bear steak generously on both sides with salt, pepper and meat tenderizer. Mix remaining ingredients. Put roast in a large ziplock bag. Add marinade. Seal and refrigerate at least overnight. Grill over medium-hot coals, turning several times and basting with reserved marinade frequently. Cook approximately 35-40 minutes, until done to your liking. Allow roast to rest for 10 minutes before slicing.

Preheat oven to 425. In a saucepan over medium heat, melt the butter. Add flour and stir thoroughly. Add chicken broth and milk. Cook until thickened. To the saucepan, add chicken, peas, carrots, onion and salt. Heat to boiling. Pour into a 1. 5 liter casserole. Top with uncooked biscuits. Bake at 425 8-10 minutes or until the biscuits are done.

Preheat oven to 350-degrees. Process pecan halves in food processor until finely ground. Combine crumbs, butter, salt, vanilla and almonds, stirring until crumbs are moistened. Press mixture evenly across 9-inch pie plate. Bake crust until crisp, about 7 minutes. Let cool completely before filling. Crust may also be wrapped tightly in plastic and frozen up to one month.

Preheat oven to 400 degrees. Cut dough into 3 - 4 oz portions. Melt butter. Crush ritz crackers into crumb size pieces. Mix together dry ingredients. Dip halibut into melted butter then into cracker mixture. Place on baking sheet. Pour remaining melted butter over halibut. Bake at 400 degrees for 12 - 15 minutes or until flaky when touched with a fork.

Preheat oven to 400 degrees. Mix manicotti, eggs, onions, parmesan cheese, nutmeg, cream-style cottage cheese, frozen spinach, mozzarella cheese, spaghetti sauce in a 6-quart dutch oven over medium heat for 1 to 2 minutes or until garlic is light brown. Add spinach. Toss well to coat. Cook and stir 2 minutes more or just until spinach is wilted and heated through. To serve, sprinkle with parmesan cheese.

Add pine nuts and garlic to blender and pulse until minced. Add basil leaves, cheese, salt and blend until smooth. Scrape sides of blender as you go to make sure everthing mixes well. Serve with your favorite pasta.

Preheat oven to 350 degrees. Prepare cake mix according to package directions, using the eggs, water, and oil. Spoon batter into 24 paper-lined muffin pan cups, filling two-thirds full. Remove 24 cherries from cherry pie filling and set aside. Spoon generous teaspoon of remaining cherry filling onto center of each cupcake. Bake in preheated 350 degree oven for 20-25 minutes. Cool in pans on wire racks for 10 minutes, then remove from pan and let cool completely. Frost cupcakes with vanilla frosting, and garnish each one with a reserved cherry.

Heat oil in a large skillet over medium-high heat. Add onion, bell pepper, mushrooms, cream of mushroom soup, french-fried onions, egg noodles, salt and pepper. Stir to combine. Cover and bake 25 minutes at 350 degrees. Remove from oven, uncover, and pour french fried onions over top. Return to oven, uncovered for five minutes. Remove from oven, uncovered for five minutes. Remove from oven, uncovered for

In a large saucepan, add honey, water, vanilla bean, nutmeg, cinnamon sticks, whole cloves, lemon, zest of, vodka, lemon juice, lemon juice, lemon juice, lemon juice, lemon juice, lemon juice, lemon juice, lemon juice, lemon juice, lemon juice, lemon juice, lemon juice, lemon juice, lemon juice, lemon juice, lemon juice, lemon juice, lemon juice, lemon juice, lemon juice, lemon juice, lemon juice, lemon juice, lemon juice, lemon juice, lemon juice, lemon juice, lemon juice, lemon juice, lemon juice, lemon juice, lemon juice, lemon juice, lemon juice, lemon juice, lemon juice, lemon juice, lemon juice, lemon juice, lemon juice, lemon juice, lemon juice, lemon juice, lemon juice, lemon juice, lemon juice, lemon juice, lemon juice, lemon juice, lemon juice, lemon juice, lemon juice, lemon juice, lemon juice, lemon juice, lemon juice, lemon juice, lemon juice, lemon juice, lemon juice, lemon juice, lemon juice, lemon juice, lemon juice, lemon juice, lemon juice, lemon juice, lemon juice, lemon juice, lemon juice, lemon juice, lemon juice, lemon juice, lemon juice, lemon juice, lemon juice, lemon juice, lemon juice, lemon juice, lemon juice, lemon juice, lemon juice, lemon juice, lemon juice, lemon juice, lemon juice, lemon juice, lemon juice, lemon juice, lemon juice, lemon juice, lemon juice, lemon juice, lemon juice, lemon juice, lemon juice, lemon juice, lemon juice, lemon juice, lemon juice, lemon juice, lemon juice, lemon juice, lemon juice, lemon juice, lemon juice, lemon juice, lemon juice, lemon juice, lemon juice, lemon juice, lemon juice, lemon juice, lemon juice, lemon juice, lemon juice, lemon juice, lemon juice,

Add all ingredients to the pan according to the order in the manufacturers directions, with the water and the sour cream put in first, and adding the dry ingredients in on top. Set crust on medium and program for the basic cycle. Press start. When the baking cycle ends, immediately remove the bread from the pan and place it on a rack. Let cool to room temperature before slicing.

In a saucepan over medium low heat, melt 3 tbls butter. Stir flour and salt into pan until creamed together. Slowly stir in cream, then stir in cream cheese, increase heat to medium. Constantly whisk until mixture becomes thick and smooth, remove from heat and set aside. In a saucepan over medium low heat, saute onions and garlic in remaining butter until transparent. Add lobster tail, chicken broth, heavy cream, cheese, unsalted butter, flour, chives, white pepper, white wine. Cook, stirring occasionally for 8 minutes. Stir prepared sauce and parmesan cheese into pan, stir until completely blended.

Melt butter in a large flameproof casserole and cook the onion over low heat for 5 minutes. Add the mushrooms, salt and pepper and continue cooking 5 minutes longer or until the mushrooms release their liquid. Turn up the heat and cook, stirring constantly, until the moisture in the mushrooms evaporates. Add the rice and stir it for a few minutes or until the grains are transparent. Pour in the stock or stock mixed with water and bring to a boil. Lower the heat, cover the pan and cook the rice for 20 minutes or until all the liquid is absorbed. Transfer half the rice to a plastic container. Serve remaining rice at once.

In a large bowl, combine vanilla yogurt, cream cheese, sugar, vanilla extract, strawberry, graham cracker crust, cream cheese, sugar, vanilla extract, strawberry, graham cracker crust, cream cheese, sugar, vanilla extract, strawberry, graham cracker crust, cream cheese, sugar, vanilla extract, strawberry, graham cracker crust, cream cheese, sugar, vanilla extract, strawberry, graham cracker crust, cream cheese, sugar, vanilla extract, strawberry, graham cracker crust, cream cheese, sugar, vanilla extract, strawberry, graham cracker crust, cream cheese, sugar, vanilla extract, strawberry, graham cracker crust, cream cheese, sugar, vanilla extract, strawberry, graham cracker crust, cream cheese, sugar, vanilla extract, strawberry, graham cracker crust, cream cheese, sugar, vanilla extract, strawberry, graham cracker crust, cream cheese, sugar, vanilla extract, strawberry, graham cracker crust, cream cheese, sugar, vanilla extract, strawberry, graham cracker crust, cream cheese, sugar, vanilla extract, strawberry, graham cracker crust, cream cheese, sugar, vanilla extract, strawberry, graham cracker crust, cream cheese, sugar, vanilla extract, strawberry, graham cracker crust, cream cheese, sugar, vanilla extract, strawberry, graham cracker crust, cream cheese, sugar, vanilla extract, strawberry, graham cracker crust, cream cheese, sugar, vanilla extract, strawberry, graham cracker crust, cream cheese, sugar, vanilla extract, strawberry, graham cracker crust, cream cheese, sugar, vanilla extract, strawberry, graham cracker crust, cream cheese, sugar, vanilla extract, strawberry, graham cracker crust, cream cheese, sugar, vanilla extract, strawberry, graham cracker crust, cream cheese,
In a large bowl, combine the mashed potatoes, egg, cheese and bacon. Shape mixture into 8 patties. Roll in bread crumbs. Place on broiler pan. Broil for 10 minutes or until delicately browned.

Preheat oven to 400f. Peel, core and slice apples into a bowl. Add brown sugar, cinnamon, water and salt. Mix well to coat apples. Place in two ramikins or small au gratin dishes, sprayed with cooking spray. Dot with butter and spread cheese over top. Bake for 20 to 30 minutes or until apples fall.

Preheat oven to 425f grease a 9x9 inche metal baking pan. In large bowl, combine first 6 ingredients. In medium bowl, whisk buttermilk, oil, and egg until blended. Stir into cornmeal mixture just until moistened. Pour batter into prepared pan. Bake 20-25 minutes or until golden and toothpick inserted in center comes out clean. Cut cornbread into 9 squares.

Spray nonstick skillet with cooking spray. Heat over med. Heat. Add potatoes, onion, green pepper, garlic clove, bacon, eggs, milk, butter, flour tortillas, cheddar cheese, salsa, enchilada saucepreparation:Mix potatoes, onion, green pepper, garlic clove, bacon, eggs, milk, butter, flour tortillas, cheddar cheese, salsa, enchilada saucepreparation:Mix potatoes, onion, green pepper, garlic clove, bacon, eggs, milk, butter, flour tortillas, cheddar cheese, salsa, enchilada saucepreparation:Mix potatoes, onion, green pepper, garlic clove, bacon, eggs, milk, butter, flour tortillas, cheddar cheese, salsa, enchilada saucepreparation:Mix potatoes, onion, green pepper, garlic clove, bacon, eggs, milk, butter, flour tortillas, cheddar cheese, salsa, enchilada saucepreparation:Mix potatoes, onion, green pepper, garlic clove, bacon, eggs, milk, butter, flour tortillas, cheddar cheese, salsa, enchilada saucepreparation:Mix potatoes, onion, green pepper, garlic clove, bacon, eggs, milk, butter, flour tortillas, cheddar cheese, salsa, enchilada saucepreparation:Mix potatoes, onion, green pepper, garlic clove, bacon, eggs, milk, butter, flour tortillas, cheddar cheese, salsa, enchilada saucepreparation:Mix potatoes, onion, green pepper, garlic clove, bacon, eggs, milk, butter, flour tortillas, cheddar cheese, salsa, enchilada saucepreparation:Mix potatoes, onion, green pepper, garlic clove, bacon,

Preheat oven to 375. Place the chicken, with the skins on, in a single layer in a shallow roasting dish and set aside. Heat the oil in a small saucepan and gently fry the green onions and garlic for about 2 minutes, until softened, but not browned. Add the honey, orange juice, orange segments and soy sauce to the pan, stirring well and cook until the honey has completely dissolved. Pour the sauce over the chicken and bake, uncovered, for about 45 minutes, basting once or twice until the chicken is cooked.

Ina bowl, combine allthe ingredients except the kaiser rolls, and mix well. Fo9rm into 4 patties. Cook in skillet, or grill over medium heat until brown on one side. Turn and repeat, sprinkling with salt, and pepper if desired. Spread buns with mayonnaise, and topping of your choice.

Heat oil in 2-quart saucepan. Add onion and garlic. Cook over medium heat for about 5 minutes, until onion wilts. Stir in cumin and pepper. Continue to cook for 2-3 minutes. Add oregano, potatoes, green chilies and chicken broth. Bring to a boil and then simmer for about 20 minutes. Use an immersion blender to puree about half of the soup. Add cooked pasta and spinach. Simmer for a few minutes until spinach is wilted.

Heat wok or deep frying pan over high heat. Add oil, onions, ginger and curry and cook 1 minute. Add stock and coconut milk and bring to simmer. Add the pumpkin, cover and cook for 5 minutes. Add the eggplants and beans and cook another 5 minutes until the pumpkin is soft. Stir in basil. Serve with rice.

Preheat oven to 350F. Place zucchini, garlic, onions, salt, pepper, eggs, flour, nonstick cooking spray in a large bowl. Mix zucchini, garlic and remaining ingredients in a large bowl. Lay evenly onto a foil lined pan. Bake uncovered at 425f for about 60 minutes or until tender and browned, turning once after first 30 minutes.

Combine the sour cream, mayonnaise and salad dressing and mix well. Squeeze the spinach to remove water. Add to the mixture and mix well. Add optional ingredient. Hollow out the bread and fill with the sour cream mixture. Arrange assorted cut up veggies and bread cubes around loaves.

Preheat oven to 350 degrees f. Pat pork chops dry with paper towels and generously season with salt and pepper. Heat a large ovenproof skillet over medium high heat. Sear chops in 1 tablespoon of oil until well browned, about 3 to 4 minutes per side. Transfer to a plate. Add remaining tablespoon of oil to skillet and cook onion and rosemary, stirring occasionally, until onions begin to caramelize and turn golden, about 5 minutes. Add garlic and cook another minute. Stir in tomatoes, anchovies, remaining salt and pepper and cook, stirring occasionally, until tomatoes break down, about 8 minutes. Return pork chops to skillet and spoon sauce over chops. Cover skillet and place in preheated oven and cook until internal meat thermometer reads 145 degrees f, about 15 minutes. Serve over polenta, egg noodles, or rice.
Preheat oven to 375 degrees. Mix all dry ingredients in large bowl. Mix dry and wet ingredients together. Pour into prepared muffin pans and bake at 375 for 20 to 25 minutes.

In a large bowl, mix the tuna lightly with the sweetcorn, onion and kidney beans. Season well with salt and pepper. Divide the salad leaves between two plates. Season lightly. Pile tuna salad on top. Drizzle over the olive oil and lemon juice. Sprinkle with chili powder. Serve with toasted bread.

Heat oil in a 10-inch skillet over medium heat. Cook pasta shells, condensed tomato soup, whipping cream, velveeta cheese, butter, garlic powder, onion powder, salt & pepper. Stir in chicken, salt, and tomatoes. Cook about 3 minutes, stirring occasionally, just until pasta shells are cooked through. Toss with pasta. Sprinkle with cheese and parsley.

Heat oil in a large non-stick skillet over medium-high heat. Add tofu, tamari soy sauce, water, five-spice powder, star anise, molasses, water, five-spice powder, star anise, molasses, water, five-spice powder, star anise, molasses, water, 5-spice powder, star anise, molasses, water, 5-spice powder, star anise, molasses, water, 5-spice powder, star anise, molasses, water, 5-spice powder, star anise, molasses, water, 5-spice powder, star anise, molasses, water, 5-spice powder, star anise, molasses, water, 5-spice powder, star anise, molasses, water, 5-spice powder, star anise, molasses, water, 5-spice powder, star anise, molasses, water, 5-spice powder, star anise, molasses, water, 5-spice powder, star anise, molasses, water, 5-spice powder, star anise, molasses, water, 5-spice powder, star anise, molasses, water, 5-spice powder, star anise, molasses, water, 5-spice powder, star anise, molasses, water, 5-spice powder, star anise, molasses, water, 5-spice powder, star anise, molasses, water, 5-spice powder, star anise, molasses, water, 5-spice powder, star anise, molasses, water, 5-spice powder, star anise, molasses, water, 5

Preheat oven to 400 degrees f. Remove chicken from marinade and discard marinade. Arrange chicken breasts in a shallow baking pan. Season with salt and pepper and roast for 25-30 minutes or until chicken is cooked through and the juices run clear when you prick it with a fork.

Place the blue grenadier fillets in a large frying pan and stir fry blue grenadier fillets until just starting to wilt. Cut 4 large squares of kitchen foi. Divide veg between them, and lay 2 pieces of fish on top of each square. In small bowl, mix together blue grenadier fillets, olive oil, dijon mustard, vinegar, salt, pepper, paprika. Pour over fish. Seal foil together and place on baking tray. Place tray in oven and cook 10 minutes. Let packets sit for a couple of minutes before opening to prevent steam burns. Open and scatter blue grenadier fillets with coriander. Serve with noodles.

In 3-quart saucepan, cover potatoes with water. Bring to a boil. Reduce heat to low and simmer 20 minutes or until potatoes are very tender. Drain. Return potatoes to saucepan. Mash. Stir in remaining ingredients.

In a crockpot, simmer the refried beans, the chopped avocado, and salsa, along with the velvetta cheese. In a skillet, brown the hamburger along with the chopped onions and garlic powder. After the hamburger is browned, add to the crockpot with the other ingredients and allow to cook for about 20 minutes on the high setting. Be sure to stir occasionally to prevent burning or sticking. Serve as a dip with tortilla chips or in mini-taco shells.

Heat 1-quart saucepan over medium-high heat. Bring to boil. Stir in whole wheat couscous, plums, scallions, goat cheese, of fresh mint, honey, balsamic vinegar, salt and pepper. Add broth and bring to boil. Cover and remove from heat. Let stand 10 to 15 minutes or until liquid is absorbed. Fluff with fork. Season to taste with salt and pepper.

Heat oven to 350 degrees f. Pat pork chops dry with paper towels and generously season with salt and pepper. Sear chops in 1 tablespoon of oil until well browned, about 3 to 4 minutes per side. Transfer to a plate. Add remaining tablespoon of oil to skillet and cook onion and rosemary, stirring occasionally, until onions begin to caramelize and turn golden, about 5 minutes. Add garlic and cook another minute. Stir in tomatoes, anchovies, remaining salt and pepper and cook, stirring occasionally, until tomatoes break down, about 8 minutes. Return pork chops to skillet and spoon sauce over chops. Cover skillet and place in preheated oven and cook until internal meat thermometer reads 145 degrees f, about 15 minutes. Serve over polenta, egg noodles, or rice.

Preheat oven to 350 degrees. Mix ingredients together in a large bowl until well-blended. Roll raisins into squares. Bake in the oven for 7 minutes. Take out of the oven, pour chocolate chips over crackers, and smooth them out after they melt. Cool in the fridge until the chocolate has hardened. Cut into squares.

In a large non-stick skillet over medium heat, melt butter and olive oil together. Add the remaining ingredients to the skillet. Stir until potatoes are evenly coated with spice mixture and onion slices are evenly distributed. Cook covered on medium heat for 15 minutes, tossing and turning the potatoes every few minutes. Potatoes will be done when slightly browned and fork-tender.

Heat one tablespoon of oil in a pan, add the mushrooms and cook over a medium heat for 2-3 minutes, or until the mushrooms have softened. Toss the mushrooms in a large bowl with the shredded chicken. Combine all the lime and soy dressing ingredients in a small jug or bowl, mix well and pour two-thirds of the dressing over the warm mushrooms. Arrange the salad leaves in a serving dish and toss through the remaining dressing. Top with the chicken and mushrooms and serve warm.

Preheat oven to 425 degrees f. And grease a 8 inch square baking pan. Sift the cornmeal, flour, baking powder and salt together. In a seperate bowl mix the egg, buttermilk oil and honey. Add the egg mixture to the dry ingredients. Beat until smooth. Pour into pan. Bake 20 minutes edges may start to brown a little.

In a large bowl, combine the macaroni, onion, garlic, onion, potatoes, carrots, kernel corn, cream of mushroom soup, water, salt and pepper, worcestershire sauce. Stir in soup, water and seasonings. Cover and simmer until veggies are tender. Serve over steamed white rice.

Preheat oven to 350 degrees. Grease a large cookie sheet. Beat butter and sugar in a large bowl with mixer at high speed, until light and fluffy. Add egg and vanilla. Beat until well blended. Combine milk, water, cinnamon stick, orange, zest of, mexican chocolate, semisweet chocolate, tangerine liqueur. Bring to a boil over medium heat. Add both kinds of chocolate and with a wire whisk, beat until chocolate is completely dissolved. Serve in mugs, adding a splash of liqueur to each serving, if desired.

Bring a large pot of water to a boil and salt it. Put olive oil in a large skillet over medium-high heat. Add garlic, shallots and pepper flakes and cook for about a minute. Add tomatoes and squash, and cook with some salt and pepper. When squash is tender about 10 minutes for shreds, 15 or so for small cubes cook pasta until it is tender. Combine sauce and pasta, and serve, garnished with parsley or parmesan.

Heat 1 tablespoon of butter in frying pan over medium heat. Add egg and fry until cooked to your preference. In a nonstick pan, fry ham until warm and lightly brown. Remove from pan and keep warm. On one slice of sourdough bread, layer slice of cheddar cheese, ham, slice of swiss cheese and fried egg. Top with other slice of bread. Brush melted butter on sandwich and place buttered side down in skillet used to fry ham. Brush melted butter on top. Heat the oil in a small saucepan and gently fry the skinless chicken breasts for about 2 minutes. Add the chicken, with the skins on, in a single layer in a shallow roasting dish and set aside. Heat the oil in a small saucepan and gently fry the skinless chicken breasts for about 2 minutes, until softened, but not browned. Add the honey, orange juice, orange segments and soy sauce to the pan, stirring well and cook until the honey has completely dissolved. Pour the sauce over the chicken and bake, uncovered, for about 45 minutes, basting once or twice until the chicken is cooked.
Preheat oven to 375 degrees. Mix all dry ingredients in large bowl. Mix dry and wet ingredients together. Pour into prepared dumplings and bake at 375 for 20 to 25 minutes.

Preheat oven to 350 degrees. Mix ingredients together in a large bowl until well-blended. Roll peanut butter mixture into tablespoon size balls. Bake 12 minutes for chewy cookies. Bake 15 minutes for crisp.

Preheat oven to 350 degrees. Spray a 9-inch pie pan with cooking spray. Mix together the milk, eggs, flour, salt, pepper, green onion. Arrange the cheese evenly over the bottom of the pie pan. Top with the crab meat. Pour the egg mixture evenly over the cheese and crab. Bake for 35 to 40 minutes, until a knife inserted in the center comes out clean. Let stand for 10 minutes before serving.

Preheat oven to 425 degrees f. Combine the frozen hash browns, cheese, and onion in a large bowl. Combine the milk, beef stock, half the melted butter, the garlic powder, salt, and pepper in another bowl. Mix until well blended, then pour the mixture over hash browns and mix well. Heat the remaining butter in large, ovenproof skillet over high heat. When the skillet is hot, spoon in the hash brown mixture. Cook the hash browns, stirring occasionally, until hot and all of the cheese has melted. Put the skillet into the oven and bake for 45 to 60 minute or until surface of hash brown is dark brown.
Preheat oven to 350 degrees.

Heat oil in 2-quart saucepan. Add onion and garlic. Cook over medium heat for about 5 minutes, until onion wilts. Stir in cumin and pepper. Continue to cook for 2-3 minutes. Add oregano, potatoes, green chilies and chicken broth. Bring to a boil and simmer slowly for 45 minutes. Serve hot with cheese sprinkled in the middle of bowl.

Place in two ramikins or small au gratin dishes, sprayed with cooking spray. Dot with butter and spread cheese over top. Bake for 20 to 30 minutes or until apples fall.

In a large non-stick skillet, cook the ground beef and garlic until the beef is no longer pink, stir frequently. Drain. In a 4-quart slow cooker, add the ground beef mixture, cheese, and tomatoes. Stir to mix. Cover and cook on low for 3-4 hours or until the cheese is melted and mixture is well heated. Stir after 2 hours. Add in the onions, stir to combine. Serve with tortilla chips.

In a large non stick skillet, heat oil over med high heat, and cook chicken thighs 3-4 minutes per side, until golden and just cooked through. Transfer chicken to serving plates. Add honey glaze to hot skillet and simmer one minute, then pour over chicken. Serve with jasmine rice.

Heat oil in a large non-stick skillet over medium-high heat. Add chicken, and sprinkle with pepper flakes. Stir fry 3 minutes. Add vegetables and teriyaki sauce. Stir fry 5 minutes or until vegetables are crisp-tender and chicken is thoroughly cooked.

In a large nonstick frying pan, add olive oil and turn on low heat. Let oil warm. Add basil and let oil absorb flavour for 5 minutes. Turn heat to medium. Sprinkle scallops with salt and pepper and add to hot oil. Add butter and cook on each side for 2 minutes. Remove from heat and add to serving dish. Sprinkle with fresh lemon. Place chives over top and serve.

Preheat oven to 350 f. Combine flour and brown sugar in a bowl. Cut in butter until crumbly. Press into bottom of an ungreased 13x9x2 inch baking pan. Top with pecans. Drizzle warmed caramel topping evenly over pecans. Bake at 350 f for 15-20 minutes or until caramel is bubbly. Place on wire rack. Sprinkle with chocolate chips. Let stand 5 minutes, then spread chocolate chips over caramel-pecan layer. Cool for at least 6 hours at room temp or until chocolate has set. Cut into bars.

In a small saucepan, combine the bacon, water chestnuts, ketchup, worcestershire sauce, soy sauce, hot sauce, sugar. Cook and stir over medium heat for 4-5 minutes or until sauce is smooth. Stir in ketchup, worcestershire sauce, soy sauce, hot sauce, sugar. Serve over ice cream.
Heat oil in a large skillet or wok over medium high heat. Add chicken. Cook and stir until lightly browned. Add remaining ingredients. Cook and stir about 10 minutes. Serve.
Preheat oven to 400 degrees. In a large mixing bowl, mash the sweet potatoes. Add the remaining ingredients and blend until smooth and creamy. Spread topping over puff and bake for ten more minutes.

Heat oil in a non stick skillet. Add onion, garlic and saute for one minute. Add spanish onions and cook until cooked and reduced, about 10 minutes on medium heat. Add optional red wine or cooking wine, mix well until reduced. Set aside once finished. When burgers are almost ready, top with portabello mushroom mixture and a slice of cheese, continue grilling or broiling until cheese is melted.

Heat oil in a pot and saut chopped garlic, onion and garlic until softened. Add turmeric, hot chicken stock, crushed tomatoes and the beans. Bring to boil and allow to simmer for 20 minutes. Puree the soup in a blender until smooth and return to the pot. Add coconut milk and heat gently.

Mix together honey, wine, cinnamon, mustard and honey in small saucepan. Stir in ham, honey and cinnamon. Cook over medium heat stirring constantly until mixture thickens and boils. Boil and stir for one minute. Remove ham about 20 minutes before done, pour drippings from pan. Cut fat surface of ham in diamond shapes. Pour glaze over or pat on with brush. Bake 20 more minutes at 325.

Spray the grill with nonstick cooking spray. Preheat the grill to medium-high or prepare a medium-high fire. To make the glaze, stir together the chutney and the rum in a cup. To make the rub, combine the cinnamon, allspice and salt in a cup. Spread the rub all over the pork, then lightly spray with nonstick spray. Place the tenderloin on the grill rack and grill, turning, 10 minutes. Continue to grill the pork, turning and brushing with the glaze, until pork reaches 160 f. Transfer to a cutting board and let rest for 5 minutes. Cut into 12 slices.

Preheat oven to 350 degrees. Grease a large cookie sheet. Beat butter and sugar in a large bowl with mixer at high speed, until light and fluffy. Add egg and vanilla. Beat until well blended. Combine flour, cocoa, cream of tartar, baking soda and salt in a medium bowl. Add to butter mixture. Mix until uniform. Mix in chopped cherries. Drop dough by tablespoonfuls onto prepared cookie sheet. Bake about 10-12 minutes or until set.

Heat oven to 375 degrees fahrenheit. In large skillet, brown beef and onion then drain. Return meat to pan. Add spaghetti sauce. Meanwhile, in a medium bowl combine mozzarella cheese and sour cream. Pour hot meat into an ungreased 12 x 8 inch dish. Spoon cheese mixture over meat. Unroll crescent roll dough over the top of the mixture. Mix parmesan cheese and butter together, then spread over the top of the dough. Bake 18-25 minutes or until golden brown.

Heat the oil in a 9-inch saute pan over moderate heat. Add the carrots and cook until lightly browned on all sides, about 3 minutes per side. Season with salt and pepper. Add the ginger, garlic, and shallots and cook over medium-low heat, stirring occasionally, until the shallots are softened, 5-7 minutes. Add the honey, orange juice, soy sauce and water. Cover with a round of waxed paper that fits snugly on the vegetables. Cook the carrots slowly on top of the stove, stirring occasionally, until the carrots are tender and the juices have formed a glaze, 30-40 minutes. Garnish with the mint.

Heat oil in a large skillet over medium-high heat. Add onion, pickles, celery seed, sour cream, mayonnaise, salt & pepper. Cook until tender, about 15 to 18 minutes. Remove from heat and set aside.

Cover skillet and place in preheated oven and cook until internal meat thermometer reads 145 degrees f, about 15 minutes. Serve over polenta, egg noodles, or rice.

Preheat oven to 375f. Heat a little oil in frying pan and brown stew meat along with onions and carrots. Remove from pan. Layer sliced potatoes, onion, carrot and meat in a 3 pint casserole, finishing with a layer of potatoes. Pour over the stock. Brush the potatoes with 1 tbsp melted butter. Cover and bake for 1 hour. Remove the hot pot from the oven. Uncover and brush the potatoes again with melted butter or dripping. Return to the oven for a further 30 minutes, uncovered, to brown the potatoes. Serve garnished with parsley.

Preheat oven to 375 degrees. Coat 8 muffin cups with pam. Mix sugar and cinnamon in small bowl. Dip each marshmallow in melted margarine and roll in sugar mix. Separate dough into triangles. Wrap one triangle around each marshmallow and pinch dough together. Place each one in a muffin cup. Drizzle extra margarine over rolls. Bake 8-12 minutes.

Preheat oven to 350 f. Combine flour and brown sugar in a bowl. Cut in pecans until crumbly. Press into bottom of an ungreased 13x9x2 inch baking pan. Top with pecans. Drizzle warmed caramel topping evenly over pecans. Bake at 350 f for 15-20 minutes or until caramel is bubbly. Place on wire rack. Sprinkle with chocolate chips. Let stand 5 minutes, then spread chocolate chips over caramel-pecan layer. Cool for at least 6 hours at room temp or until chocolate has set. Cut into bars.

Preheat oven to 350 degrees f. For the filling, mix the two filling ingredients in a bowl, then press onto bottom of 9 inch springform pan. Chill to set. For the filling, beat cream cheese on medium speed until fluffy. Beat in sugar until blended, then beat in eggs until blended. Stir in white chocolate, cranberries, zest & vanilla. Pour into prepared filling & bake 45-50 minutes or until center is almost set. Cool in pan for 30 minutes, then refrigerate. Run knife around sides of pan to loosen, then chill 4 hours or more. Remove rim & cut into wedges. Refrigerate leftovers.

Preheat the oven to 375f and butter a baking pan. Press a clove into each chop, then add the chops to the pan, followed by the wine, celery leaves, and bay leaves. Bake the chops for 30 minutes. Meanwhile, heat the butter in a frying pan and saute the diced celery for 5 minutes, tehn add the apples and brown sugar. Turn the heat to low and cook for 10 minutes, or until just tender. After 30 minutes, remove the pork chops, discard the bay and celery leaves and sprinkle cheese on each chop. Baste with juices and broil a few minutes to brown. Add a few pan juices to the apple-celery mixture, and serve as a side with the swiss cheese and apple butter.
Preheat oven to 350 degrees. Bake for about 25-30 minutes or until the cheese is completely melted.

Heat one tablespoon of oil in a pan, add the anchovies, black olives, capers, cauliflower, red bell pepper, garlic cloves, herbs, olive oil, red wine vinegar and mix well. Add the anchovies, black olives, capers, cauliflower, red bell pepper, garlic cloves, herbs, olive oil, red wine vinegar and mix well. Add the anchovies, black olives

In a gallon glass mayonnaise jar, or other type of crock that can be sealed completely, mix all the ingredients and seal with electrical or duct tape so no aid can get in or liquid can evaporate. Shake gently twice a day until the sugar is dissolved then about every other day so that the mixture is evenly flavored. Now the hard part -- let sit, for 2 months. Then strain through 4 layers of cheesecloth in a colander. After sediment has settled, siphon off the clear cordial mixture and decant. This is really smooth and friends are still asking if i have the recipe. I hope that you enjoy it.

Place pork tenderloin on a broiler pan and broil until golden, pour in ketchup, soy sauce, vinegar and brown sugar. Heat until blended. Pour over ribs. Cover, cook on low 8 hours. Cook noodles per package directions. Serve ribs over noodles.

Preheat oven to 325 degrees f. In 2 pans place tomato halves cut side up. Sprinkle with oil, salt and pepper, onion, garlic, oregano, thyme, red wine, and herbs. Bake tomatoes for 2 hours. Check the tomatoes after 1 hour and turn down the heat if they seem to be cooking too quickly. Then turn the oven to 400 degrees and bake another 30 minutes. Remove from the oven and process tomatoes through a food mill using a medium dye over a small saucepan. Discard skins. Add wine, bring to a boil, reduce heat to low and cook for 5 minutes.

Heat a small skillet over medium-high heat and add the romano cheese. Cook, stirring constantly, until golden, 3 to 4 minutes. Immediately remove from the pan. Place the romano cheese, garlic, basil, walnuts and olive oil in a blender or food processor and process until smooth. Stop and scrape down the sides. Add the grated cheese and crushed red-pepper flakes and pulse a few times to make a thick paste. Transfer to a bowl and fold in the tomatoes. Season with salt and pepper.

Add all ingredients to the pan according to the order in the manufacturers directions, with the water and the sour cream put in first, and adding the dry ingredients in on top. Set crust on medium and program for the basic cycle. Press start. When the baking cycle ends, immediately remove the bread from the pan and place it on a rack. Let cool to room temperature before slicing.

Preheat oven to 350 degrees. Brown beef and onions in skillet. Drain. Mix in tomato sauce, garlic and oregano. Place in a 2-quart casserole dish. Top with corn. Then spread mashed potatoes over the corn. Lay cheese over the mashed potatoes in a single layer. Bake for about 25-30 minutes or until the cheese is completely melted.

In a small bowl, combine all ingredients, except the cabbage, and cook until crisp. Remove and reserve bacon. Add sugar, vinegar, and wine to bacon fat. Stir and cook until sugar is dissolved. Pour this hot mixture over the cabbage. Toss with vegetable oil, salt, pepper, and caraway seeds. Sprinkle crumbled bacon over mixture. Serve at room temperature.

In a medium nonstick saucepan, heat oil over medium heat. Add onion and cook until soft. Add quinoa and stir once. Quickly return to a boil. Reduce heat to low, cover and simmer 15-20 minutes, until water is absorbed and quinoa is tender. Remove from heat and let stand 3 minutes. Add parsley, mint, currants and orange zest. Stir with a fork to combine and fluff up grain.

Heat olive oil in a large skillet over medium heat. Add onions and saut until soft, about 5 minutes. Add potatoes and 2 cups water. Bring to boil. Cover and simmer until potatoes are tender, stirring occasionally, about 25 minutes. Remove from heat. Add crme frache and 1 tablespoon butter. Stir gently to blend, being careful not to break up potatoes. Season with salt and pepper. Can be made 2 hours ahead- let stand at room temperature and rewarm over low heat before serving. Sprinkle liberally with salt and pepper, then add other seasonings as desired. Toss together to be sure all of potatoes are coated with butter and seasonings. Return to oven until potatoes are crisp and tender.

Preheat oven to 350 degrees. Grease a large cookie sheet. Beat butter and sugar in a large bowl with mixer at high speed, until light and fluffy. Add egg and vanilla. Beat until well blended. Combine cream cheese, butter, powdered sugar, brown sugar, vanilla extract, semisweet mini chocolate chips, pecans, honey, chocolate graham cracker. Add to butter mixture. Mix well. Chill for at least 2 hours. Serve with crackers.

In a skillet, heat butter or oil. Add in onions. Fry over medium heat until they are soft and golden brown. Prepare gravy and keep warm. Grill or fry hamburgers to desired degree of doneness. Cook french fries in the oven according to package directions. Right before the burgers and fries are done, toast the bread. Place 1 slice on each of 2 plates. Remove fries from oven and place half on each slice of toast. Cut each burger into bite-size pieces and place on top of fries. Ladle cup gravy over each serving, top each with half the fried onions, and serve immediately.

Heat oil in 2-quart saucepan. Add onion and garlic. Cook over medium heat for about 5 minutes, until onion wilts. Stir in cumin and pepper. Continue to cook for 2-3 minutes. Add oregano, potatoes, green chilies and chicken broth. Bring to a boil and simmer slowly for 45 minutes. Serve hot with cheese sprinkled in the middle of bowl.
Preheat oven to 375 degrees. Mix all dry ingredients in large bowl. Mix dry and wet ingredients together. Pour batter into prepared muffin pans and bake at 375 for 20 to 25 minutes.
In a slow cooker add 1 cup of milk to the slow cooker. Add 1 cup of milk to the slow cooker.

Preheat the oven to 375. Place the chicken, with the skins on, in a single layer in a shallow roasting dish and set aside. Heat the oil in a small saucepan and gently fry the green onions and garlic for about 2 minutes, until softened, but not browned. Add the honey, orange segments and soy sauce to the pan, stirring well and cook until the honey has completely dissolved. Pour the sauce over the chicken and bake, uncovered, for about 45 minutes, basting once or twice until the chicken is cooked.

In a large mixing bowl, cream the butter until smooth. Add in the sugars. Beat on low for 2 minutes. Add in the milk, syrup, and vanilla. Beat 3-5 minutes until smooth and creamy. Use immediately or store, covered, at room temperature for up to 2 days. Reportedly, the icing tastes better if made the day before because the brown sugar gives the icing a slightly grainy texture that improves if allowed to set overnight.

Preheat oven to 350 degrees. In a large mixing bowl, cream together the butter, sugars, eggs and vanilla. In another bowl, mix together the flour, salt, baking powder and baking soda. Combine the wet and dry ingredients. Stir in chocolate chips. With your fingers, place golf ball-sized dough portions 2-inches apart on an ungreased cookie sheet. Bake 9-10 minutes or just until edges are light brown.

Place chicken in a single layer in a shallow non-reactive pan. Pour marinade over, cover and refrigerate 8 hours or overnight. To cook, drain chicken, reserving marinade. Place chicken over medium-hot coals and grill 6-7 minutes per side, until internal temperature is 165 degrees fahrenheit. While chicken is grilling, place reserved marinade in a saucepan over medium heat and bring to a boil. Reduce heat and simmer 8 minutes, or until chicken has finished cooking. Spoon sauce over chicken and serve.

Preheat oven to 375 degrees. Place a skillet over high heat and add oil. Saute onion for 3 to 4 minutes. Add mushrooms and garlic and continue to saute until mushrooms have released their liquid and they are golden. Add chicken stock and bring to boil. Pour mushroom and stock mixture orzo and rosemary into a 8x8 baking dish. Season with salt and pepper and bake 35 minutes until liquid is absorbed.

Preheat grill on high heat. Lay out ground chuck in a single layer and season well with salt and pepper. Divide chuck into four portions. Wrap each piece of manchego in a 4-inch square piece of ham. Heat oil in a frying pan over medium heat. Add each ham-and-cheese bundle and fry, turning, until ham is crisped and cheese is beginning to melt. Allow to cool slightly, fold meat around each bundle to form hamburgers about 1 inch thick. Grill burgers for about 4 to 5 minutes a side or until just cooked through.

Preheat oven to 350 degrees c. In a large bowl sift together flour and baking soda, set aside. In a large bowl, combine butter and both sugars. Beat on medium speed until light and fluffy, about 3 minutes. Reduce speed to low, add salt, vanilla, and eggs. Beat until well mixed, about 1 minute. Add flour mixture, mix until just combined. Stir in chocolate chips. Drop heaping spoonfuls about 2 inches apart onto baking trays lined with parchment paper. Bake until golden around the edges and soft in the middle, about 8-10 minutes.

Heat the oil in a saucepan. Add onion, peanut oil, mango, white vinegar, orange juice, banana, ginger, raisins, brown sugar, serrano chili. Simmer for ten minutes then turn off heat. Cool for a few minutes and then pour the mixture into a blender or food processor and blend until the mixture is the consistency of chutney. Pour into sterilised chutney jar and store in fridge. The mango and banana chutney will last for a couple of weeks in the fridge.

Preheat oven to 350 degrees. In large bowl, mash the bananas, stir in oats, dates, oil and vanilla. Mix well and allow to sit for 15 minutes. Drop by tspfuls onto ungreased cookie sheet. Bake for 15-20 minutes. In combining the ingredients, i personally use my food processor. I just toss everything in and let it mix.

Preheat oven to 375 degrees. Cook noodles in accordance with package and drain. In a medium mixing bowl, combine melted soup and milk and stir until well blended. In 13 x 9 baking dish, combine ham, cooked noodles, liquid soup mixture and half of the cheese. Bake for 20 minutes. Sprinkle remaining cheese over top of casserole. Dot with butter. Bake for additional 10 minutes or until cheese is melted and bubbly.

Heat olive oil over medium heat. Saut crushed garlic for 1-2 minutes. Stir in tomato sauce. Add salt, pepper, and pesto. Add cream cheese and stir or whisk well until fully melted. Stir parmesan cheese until melted. Add cream and stir well.

Cook brisket cholent in a large saucepan over medium heat. Add beef and onion. Cook, stirring frequently, for 5 minutes. Add garlic, mushrooms and carrots. Cook another 5 minutes. Add pilaf mix, orange juice and beef broth. Bring to a boil, then reduce heat and simmer, covered, for 20 minutes or until liquid has been absorbed.
Place mushroom and swiss on top of crostini toast appetizers. Cover and bake at 400 f or 200 c for 1 hour. Uncover and bake 10 more minutes or until mushrooms are tender.

Preheat oven to 350f.
