Preheat oven to 350 degrees. In a large mixing bowl, with electric mixer at medium speed, beat together butter and shortening until light and fluffy. Add sugar and cream together until very light. Add vanilla, scraping down sides of bowl as needed. Add eggs one at a time, beating well after each egg. Gradually fold in flour until a soft, workable dough forms. Shape into balls and place on cookie sheets. Dip the bottom of a flat bottomed glass in sugar and use it to mash down the balls of dough. Bake in preheated oven until done. Immediately remove from pan to cool.

Combine all of the ingredients, except the coconut, together in a blender. Cover and blend on low speed for 3 minutes. Pour into a greased 9-inch pie pan. Let stand about 5 minutes then sprinkle with coconut. Bake at 350 degrees for 40 minutes. Serve warm or cool.

Combine all of the ingredients for the sauce in a small bowl. Brush over the chicken. Broil the chicken for 10 minutes each side, 2 inches or so from the heat. Brush frequently with the sauce. Bake chicken for 10 minutes each side, 2 inches or so from the heat. Serve.

Heat grill. In a small bowl, stir together all glaze ingredients. Sprinkle chicken with salt and pepper. Brush chicken generously with glaze. Place chicken on gas grill over medium or on charcoal grill 4 to 6 inches from medium coals. Cover grill. Cook 8-12 minutes or until juices run clear, turning once and brushing occasionally with glaze.

Add all ingredients to the pan according to the order in the manufacturers directions, with the water and the sour cream put in first, and adding the dry ingredients in on top. Set crust on medium and program for the basic cycle. Press start. When the baking cycle ends, immediately remove the bread from the pan and place it on a rack. Let cool to room temperature before slicing.
Place roast and onion in crock pot sprayed with pam. Add cornstarch, water and cornstarch mixture. Cover. Cook on high 1 hour and then low 6 hours. Slice and serve.

Preheat oven to 400 degrees c. Place the salmon on a broiler pan and baste with the sauce. Let sit for 15 minutes. Broil them until cooked through, about 8 minutes, basting again with the glaze. Remove the salmon from the heat and baste once more with the glaze before serving.

Preheat oven to 450 degrees f or grill to medium-high. Sprinkle both sides of steak with garlic powder and pepper. Cut in thin strips. Combine beef and onions with teriyaki sauce. Bake 12 to 15 minutes on a cookie sheet in oven or grill 7 to 9 minutes in covered grill. Serve immediately over rice. Makes 4 servings.

In a small bowl, combine cabbage, carrot, cilantro, lime juice, apple cider vinegar, salt, chili powder. Add salt and pepper to taste. Taste, adjust seasoning, taste, taste, taste. Add the mixture to the cabbage, toss well, refrigerate overnight or for several hours, and make sure its well and tightly covered. Serve very cold.

Heat the oven to 400f. Put the chicken skin-side-up in a small roasting tin. Mix together the garlic, thyme and butter and dot over the chicken. Scatter around the red onions and pancetta and drizzle with oil. Roast for 20 minutes until the chicken has cooked through and the onions are softened. Divide the salad between 4 plates and top with the red onions, pancetta and chicken.

In a large saucepan over medium heat, melt the butter with the olive oil. Add in the mushrooms and garlic. Saute about 5 minutes, until wilted. Add in spinach. Toss with 2 forks, about 5 minutes, until wilted. Season with salt and pepper. Mix well. Serve immediately.

Heat salted water in a large saucepan until boiling. Cook the beans until tender, about 7 minutes. Drain beans. Set aside to cool. Whisk together the garlic, vinegar, mustard, salt and pepper to taste in a small bowl. Slowly whisk in the olive oil, adding in a steady stream, until smooth. Combine the reserved beans, green onions, mushrooms and parsley in a large bowl. Pour dressing over vegetables. Toss lightly. Chill 30 minutes before serving.

Preheat oven to 350 degrees. Grease a 9 x 5-inch loaf pan. Beat butter and sugar in a large bowl with mixer at high speed, until light and fluffy. Add egg and vanilla. Beat until well blended. Combine flour, cocoa, cream of tartar, baking soda and salt in a medium bowl. Add to butter mixture. Mix until uniform. Mix in chopped cherries. Drop dough by tablespoonfuls onto prepared cookie sheet. Bake about 10-12 minutes or until set.

Heat oil in a 10-inch skillet over medium heat. Cook broccoli, onion, garlic and carrot in oil about 10 minutes, stirring occasionally, until broccoli is crisp- tender. Stir in chicken, salt, and tomatoes. Cook about 3 minutes, stirring occasionally, just until chicken is hot. Toss with pasta. Sprinkle with cheese and parsley.

Preheat oven to 425f grease a 9x9 inche metal baking pan. In large bowl, combine first 6 ingredients. In medium bowl, whisk buttermilk, oil, and egg until blended. Stir into cornmeal mixture just until moistened. Pour batter into prepared pan. Bake 20-25 minutes or until golden and toothpick inserted in center comes out clean. Cut cornbread into 9 squares.

In a large saucepan, combine apples, juice, boiling water, cinnamon, sugar crystals, vanilla extract, honey. Bring to a boil. Reduce heat to medium and simmer until mixture has reduced by half. Test consistency by dipping a spoon into the mixture and then rubbing your finger across it. You will be able to tell when it has thickened. Cooking time will vary. You may this in sterile jars or let it cool and keep in the refrigerator.

Heat grill to medium-high heat. Mix mayo and basil. Refrigerate until ready to use. Combine meat and garlic. Shape into 8 thin patties. Top 4 patties with cheese. Cover with remaining patties. Pinch edges together to seal. Grill 7 to 9 minute on each side or until burgers are done. Spread buns with mayo mixture. Fill with lettuce, tomatoes, burgers and peppers.

In a large saucepan over medium heat, melt the butter with the olive oil. Add in the mushrooms and garlic. Saute about 5 minutes, until wilted. Add in spinach. Toss with 2 forks, about 5 minutes, until wilted. Season with salt and pepper. Mix well. Serve immediately.

Line a 9 x 13 pan with aluminum foil. Preheat oven to 400. Place saltine crackers in pan in rows. I usually can fit about 24 in the pan. In a saucepan, bring the butter and sugar to a boil. After it begins boiling, boil for 3 minutes. Immediately pour the butter-sugar mixture on the crackers. Bake in the oven for 7 minutes. Take out of the oven, pour chocolate chips over crackers, and smooth them out after they melt. Cool in the fridge until the chocolate has hardened. Cut into squares.

Heat oil in skillet over medium high heat. Saut onion and garlic about 6 minutes until tender. Add flour and cook 2 minutes, stirring frequently. Gradually whisk in milk. Increase heat to high and whisk 2-3 minutes, or until mixture boils and begins to thicken. Reduce heat to low and stir in remaining ingredients, except cheese. Season with salt and pepper to taste.

Scoop the avocado out of the skin into a bowl. Coarsely mash with fork or potato masher. Add all other ingredients except the lime juice. Lightly blend - authentic guac is chunky, not pureed. Squeeze in lime juice, mix gently and taste for seasoning adjustments.

Heat oil over medium heat. Saut garlic until soft, being careful not to let it burn. Add sliced mushrooms and saut until they look fairly cooked and shiny. Add almonds and saut for a couple more minutes. Finally, add frozen green beans and splash of soy sauce. Stir frequently until beans are just cooked and, of course, no longer frozen. If not on the south beach diet or watching sugar intake, you could add oyster sauce or other asian condiment to the mixture.

In a large skillet over medium heat, cook bacon until crisp. Remove bacon. Crumble and set aside. Drain, reserving 2 tablespoons of drippings. Add potatoes, green pepper, onion, salt and pepper to drippings. Cook and stir for 2 minutes. Cover and cook, stirring occasionally, until potatoes are browned and tender, about 15 minutes. Make six wells in the potato mixture. Break one egg into each well. Cover and cook on low heat for 8-10 minutes or until eggs are completely set. Sprinkle with cheese and bacon.

Preheat oven to 400 degrees f or grill to medium-high. Sprinkle both sides of steak with garlic powder and pepper. Cut in thin strips. Combine beef tenderloin steaks and garlic powder with teriyaki sauce. Center one-fourth of the steak mixture on each sheet of foil. Bring up foil sides. Double fold top and ends to seal packet, leaving room for heat circulation inside. Repeat to make four packets. Bake 12 to 15 minutes on a cookie sheet in oven or grill 7 to 9 minutes in covered grill. Serve immediately over rice. Makes 4 servings.

In a large bowl, combine cream cheese, ham, cheddar cheese, spring onions, black pepper, macadamia nuts. Beat until combined. Cover and chill one hour. Mould with hands and shape into a log. Insert almonds along the top. Some times i add a little more beer and spoon into little crocks-- chill 3 to 24 hours.

Heat oil over medium heat. Saut garlic until soft, being careful not to let it burn. Add sliced mushrooms and saut until beans are just cooked and, of course, no longer frozen. If not on the south beach diet or watching sugar intake, you could add oyster sauce or other asian condiment to the mixture.

In a small bowl, using a fork or potato masher, mash the avocados until chunky. Add the onion, cilantro, bell pepper, and chile. In a small bowl, combine the lime juice and package of hidden valley original ranch salad dressing & seasoning mix. Add to the avocado mixture along with the pepper and stir gently to combine. Transfer the dip to a serving bowl and place a piece of plastic wrap directly on the surface of the guacamole, pressing to eliminate any air pockets. Serve at room temperature. This dip is best when made within 8 hours of serving, but it can be prepared up to 1 day in advance. Cover and refrigerate. Remove from the refrigerator 30 minutes before serving, but keep covered until ready to serve.

Heat the oil in a large saute pan. Add the chicken and onion, and cook together until golden. Add the spices and red pepper, and cook for 1 minute. Cover and simmer 20-25 minutes until the chicken is tender. Serve with rice or mashed potatoes.

Heat oven to 400 degrees. Grease round baking dish. Melt butter in skillet over med-lo heat. Add onion and red pepper, cook until soft. Add ham, cook 2 mins more. Beat eggs and milk in bowl. Stir in cheese and add veggies and ham. Season with salt and pepper. Transfer to prepared dish. Bake 20 minutes or until top is puffy and brown. Cut into wedges and serve warm.

Heat oven to 350 degrees f. Pat pork chops dry with paper towels and generously season with salt and pepper. Transfer to a plate. Add remaining tablespoon of oil to skillet and cook onion and rosemary, stirring occasionally, until onions begin to caramelize and turn golden, about 5 minutes. Add garlic and cook another minute. Stir in tomatoes, anchovies, remaining salt and pepper and cook, stirring occasionally, until tomatoes break down, about 8 minutes. Return pork chops to skillet and spoon sauce over chops. Cover skillet and place in preheated oven and cook until internal meat thermometer reads 145 degrees f, about 15 minutes. Serve over polenta, egg noodles, or rice.

Preheat oven to 350-degrees. Process pie crust in food processor until finely ground. Combine crumbs, butter, salt, vanilla and almonds, stirring until crumbs are moistened. Press mixture evenly across 9-inch pie plate. Bake crust until crisp, about 7 minutes. Let cool completely before filling. Crust may also be wrapped tightly in plastic and frozen up to one month.

Heat oil in a large skillet over medium-high heat. Add onions and cook until softened, about 5 minutes. Add garlic and cook until softened, about 5 minutes. Add salt and pepper and cook until softened, about 5 minutes. Add cumin, chili, cilantro, sour cream, cheddar cheese, flour tortillas and cook until softened, about 5 minutes. Preheat oven to 350f. Spray 13x9 pan with cooking spray. Drain butter beans and pour into pan. Add all other ingredients and mix well. Bake for 1 hour or until brown and bubbling.

Heat oil for deep frying in a frying pan and drop large spoonfuls of the mixture as for small pancakes and fry until golden brown on both sides and cooked in the middle, about 5 minutes. Drain well on paper towels and keep hot until ready to serve. Eat immediately.

In a large non-stick skillet over medium heat, melt butter and olive oil together. Add the remaining ingredients to the skillet. Stir until potatoes are evenly coated with spice mixture and onion slices are evenly distributed. Cook covered on medium heat for 15 minutes, tossing and turning the potatoes every few minutes. Potatoes will be done when slightly browned and fork-tender.

Place thin sliced onions over pork chops. Mix sour cream, dry mustard and salt. Pour mixture over onions. Bake uncovered for 90 minutes, or until pork chops are well done.

Preheat oven to 350f. Season chicken breasts with garlic powder, salt and pepper. Wrap each chicken breast in 1 strip of bacon and place in a 9x13x2-inch baking dish. In a small bowl, mix the sour cream and soup. Spoon mixture over the chicken and bake uncovered for 40 to 50 minutes or until slightly brown on top. Serve with hot cooked rice, if desired.

Heat the oil in a heavy pan over medium heat. Add the sausage pieces and cook until brown, about 5 minutes. Add the onions, green peppers, and celery. Cook for 3 minutes. Add the water, tomato sauce, salt and pepper. Heat to boiling. Stir in the rice. Reduce heat to simmer. Cook covered, until rice is tender, about 30 minutes. Remove from heat and keep covered until time to serve.

Place the onion, rinsed beans, jalapeno, garlic, salt, pepper, and cumin into a slow cooker. Pour in the water and stir to combine. Cook on high for 8 hours, adding more water as needed. Once the beans have cooked, strain them, and reserve the liquid. Mash the beans with a potato masher, adding the reserved water as needed to attain desired consistency.

Spray nonstick skillet with cooking spray. Heat over med. Heat. Add ground beef mixture, cheese, and tomatoes. Stir to mix. Cover and cook on low for 3-4 hours or until the cheese is melted and mixture is well heated. Stir after 2 hours. Add in the onions, stir to combine. Serve with tortilla chips.

Preheat oven to 350 degrees. After browning and crumbling the egg drop soup, place it in the bottom of a 9x13 baking dish. Beat eggs, add cheese and salsa verde. Pour egg mixture over the sausage. Bake for 45 minutes or until eggs are set.

Preheat oven to 350. In a small bowl combine the garlic and oil and mix well. In a small bowl combine parsley, thyme, marjoram and paprika. Add parmesan. Mix well. Cut each loaf lengthwise. Brush with garlic oil. Sprinkle herb mix on top of garlic oil. Wrap loosely in foil and place on baking sheet. Bake until heated through, about 10-15 minutes. Unwrap and slice.

Heat the oil in a saucepan. Add butter, scallions, jalapeno chile, garlic, thyme, chicken broth, large shrimp. Add shrimp, sprinkle with the orange juice, orange zest, salt and pepper and remaining olive oil. Roast until the shrimp turns pink, about 10 minutes. Add shrimp, sprinkle with the orange zest, salt and pepper and remaining olive oil

Place potatoes in a large pot and cover with water. Bring to a boil then cover and reduce heat. Simmer for 20-25 minutes or until the potatoes are tender. Drain well, then return potatoes to the pot. Add the butter, milk and salt and mash well. Stir in parmesan cheese.

Melt butter in a heavy saucepan over low heat. Add flour, stirring until smooth. Cook 1 minute, stirring constantly. Gradually add milk. Cook over medium heat, stirring constantly until mixture is thickened and bubbly. Stir in cheddar cheese, salt, dry mustard, and paprika. Gradually stir approx one-fourth of hot mixture into beaten egg. Add to remaining hot mixture. Cook mixture over low heat 1 minute. Serve over toast points.

Preheat oven to 375 degrees. Grease 8x8 square pan. Melt butter and cool slightly and add milk and beaten egg, set to the side. In bowl, sift the next four ingredients, 2 times. Add butter, milk, and egg mixture and stir only enough to smooth out any lumps. Combine the remaining sugar and cinnamon for the topping, in a small bowl or in a ziploc bag. Pour batter into greased pan and sprinkle the mixture of sugar and cinnamon over the top and bake 12 to 15 minutes.

Add all ingredients to the pan according to the order in the manufacturers directions, with the water and the white flour put in first, and adding the dry ingredients in on top. Set crust on medium and program for the basic cycle. Press start. When the baking cycle ends, immediately remove the bread from the pan and place it on a rack. Let cool to room temperature before slicing.

Preheat oven to 375. Place the chicken, with the skins on, in a single layer in a shallow roasting dish and set aside. Heat the oil in a small saucepan and gently fry the green onions and garlic for about 2 minutes, until softened, but not browned. Add the honey, orange segments and soy sauce to the pan, stirring well and cook until the honey has completely dissolved. Pour the sauce over the chicken and bake, uncovered, for about 45 minutes, basting once or twice until the chicken is cooked.

Preheat oven to 450 degrees. Chop onions and slice mushrooms. Melt margarine in skillet. Saute onions until transparent. Add mushrooms. Cover and cook 10 minutes. Allow to cool. Mix together egg, flour, non-dairy milk and wine. Salt and pepper to taste. Pour into pie crust. Form lattice strips from second crust and place on top of quiche. Bake for 2 minutes.

Add the honey, orange juice, orange segments and soy sauce to the pan, stirring well and cook until the honey has completely dissolved. Pour the sauce over the chicken and bake, uncovered, for about 45 minutes, basting once or twice until the chicken is cooked.

Preheat oven to 375 degrees. Mix all dry ingredients in large bowl. Combine wet ingredients in a bowl. Mix dry and wet ingredients together. Pour into prepared muffin pans and bake at 375 for 20 to 25 minutes.

Preheat oven to 400f. Peel, core and slice apples into a bowl. Add brown sugar, cinnamon, water and salt. Mix well to coat apples. Place in two ramikins or small au gratin dishes, sprayed with cooking spray. Dot with butter and spread cheese over top. Bake for 20 to 30 minutes or until apples fall.

In a 2qt saucepan, mix the brown gravy according to package directions. Once gravy is thickened, add the cream of mushroom soup and sour cream. Blend well. Place the thawed or partially thawed meatballs in a crockpot. Add the gravy to crockpot and heat on low. May be served over rice, noodles, or potatoes.

Place potatoes in water and 1 tsp salt and simmer until tender, about 15 to 18 minutes. Drain and run under cold water to cool. Cut into quarters. Meanwhile, cook bacon in skillet untel crisp. Crumble when cooled. Whisk oil, vinegar, mustard, remaining salt, and pepper in a large bowl. Toss with the potatoes, bacon and parsley.

Preheat oven to 325f. Combine cream cheese, sugar and eggs in a small bowl. Beat until fluffy. Place crust on baking sheet. Pour mixture into crust. Bake 25 to 30 minutes. Remove from oven. Cool. Spread blueberry filling on top. Garnish with whipped topping. Chill 3 hours.
Preheat oven to 375 degrees. Add bacon, potatoes, fresh broccoli, celery, carrots, onion, kielbasa, salt and pepper. Bake for 25-30 minutes.

Heat a medium size saucepan over medium heat. Add egg yolks, water, fresh lemon juice, unsalted butter, cayenne pepper, salt, fresh ground white pepper. Add the heavy cream and let reduce by half. Turn heat to low, add the gorgonzola and stir until it melts. Season, to taste, with salt and pepper.

Place skewers on baking sheet and broil, turning and basting with marinade once, for about 4 minutes or until golden and fish flakes easily when tested. Alternatively, cook skewers on oiled grill pan on grill. Before serving, sprinkle with green onion and sesame seeds, if using.

Heat oil in a 10-inch skillet over medium heat. Cook broccoli, onion, garlic and carrot in oil about 10 minutes, stirring occasionally, until broccoli is crisp- tender. Stir in chicken, salt, and tomatoes. Cook about 3 minutes, stirring occasionally, just until broccoli is hot. Toss with pasta. Sprinkle with cheese and parsley. Serve or store in fridge for up to 24 hours.

In a large nonstick frying pan, add olive oil and turn on low heat. Let oil warm. Add scallops with salt and pepper and add to hot oil. Add butter and cook on each side for 2 minutes. Remove from heat and add to serving dish. Sprinkle with fresh lemon. Place chives over top and serve.

Combine all ingredients in a medium saucepan and cook over medium heat intil cranberries pop. Reduce heat to low. Cook, stirring occasionally, until cranberries release their juices, about 15 minutes. If the cranbgerry sauce becomes too thick, add water until the desired consistency is reached. Transfer to a bowl to cool.

Heat oil in a large nonstick frying pan over medium heat. Add mushrooms and saute for about 2 minutes, just until a little browned. Remove sausage and place on a paper towel. Meanwhile, whisk together eggs, milk and baking powder. When sausage is removed from pan, add egg mixture. Sprinkle with mushroom and spinach. Top with grated cheese. Cover pan with lid and turn heat down to medium-low. Check after about 3 minutes and see if omelette has set - the middle should not jiggle. Add salt and pepper to taste.

Place the rice vinegar, soy sauce, fresh ginger, cod fish fillets, coarse salt, fresh ground pepper, scallions in a nonreactive saucepan. Bring the mixture to a boil, reduce the heat to medium and cook for 15 to 20 minutes or until the sauce forms a glaze. Set aside. Preheat the broiler. Place the salmon on a broiler pan and baste with the sauce. Let sit for 15 minutes. Broil them until cooked through, about 8 minutes, basting again with the glaze. Remove the salmon from the heat and baste once more with the glaze before serving.

Place chicken breast side up in 4-6 quart slow cooker. Squeeze remaining 3 lemon halves over chicken and sprinkle with salt, pepper, and paprika. Cover with lid and cook on high heat setting for 1 hour. Reduce heat to low, and cook six hours or until chicken is tender. Discard the rosemary and lemon half. Serve chicken with celery and onion.

Heat oil in a pot and saut chopped tomato, onion, v8 vegetable juice, water, tomato soup, mixed vegetables, italian seasoning, salt, ground black pepper, pasta. Bring to boil and allow to simmer for 20 minutes. Puree the soup in a blender until smooth and return to the pot. Preheat oven to 350f. Mix salt, meat, egg, and torn up bread together. Fill each muffin cup of muffin pan almost to the top. Top with a onion ring and ketchup in the middle of the ring. Place in oven until thoroughly cooked, about 20-30 minutes.

Preheat oven to 400 degrees. In a medium bowl, whisk eggs until well beaten and slightly frothy. Whisk in milk, chives and black pepper. Set aside. In a large ovenproof skillet, heat olive oil or butter over medium heat until hot but not smoking. Add egg mixture to skillet and then quickly arrange remaining ingredients on top of eggs. Cook for 3 minutes on the stovetop without stirring. Transfer to oven. Bake until the top is golden brown and the frittata is set, about 30 minutes. Let cool slightly before serving.

Preheat oven to 350f. Mix the first six ingredients for crust. Place half of mix in a greased 9x13 inch pan. Bake crust for 10 minutes. Melt caramels and whipping cream. Place chocolate chips over baked crust, drizzel caramel over chips, then place the remaining crust mixture on top of the caramel. Bake another 10-15 minutes at 350 degrees. Cool.

Preheat oven to 350 degrees. Mix together cake mix, egg, butter, powdered sugar, eggs, cream cheese, vanilla, and vanilla until smooth. Spread mixture over bottom layer. Bake 30-40 minutes, until top layer turns a light golden brown.

Preheat oven to 350 degrees. Mix ingredients together in a large bowl until well-blended. Roll spelt flour mixture into tablespoon size balls. Bake 12 minutes for chewy biscuits. Bake 15 minutes for crisp.
Cook noodles in a 1. 5 quart casserole dish. Sprinkle cheese over top of casserole. Bake 30 minutes at 350 degrees.

Heat the oil in a heavy pan over medium heat. Add the sausage pieces and cook until brown, about 5 minutes. Add the onions, green peppers, and celery. Cook for 3 minutes. Add the water, tomato sauce, salt and pepper. Heat to boiling. Stir in the rice. Reduce heat to simmer. Cook covered, until rice is tender, about 30 minutes. Remove from heat and keep covered until time to serve.
Heat the oil in a saucepan. Add shrimp. Toss gently to coat. Marinate at least two hours or overnight. Grill for 2 minutes per side.

In a large skillet, saute the chicken in oil until no longer pink. Stir in the soup, water, salt and pepper. Bring to a boil. Remove from heat and stin in sour cream. Serve over toasted english muffins. Can also serve over cooked noodles. Sprinkle with cayenne pepper or paprika.

In a food processor puree the shallots with the shallot, the anchovies, lemon juice and the cayenne. With the motor running add the olive oil in a stream. Add the scotch and the butter cubes. Blend the mixture until it is combined well. Pack the mixture into small ramekins or a crock, and chill it, covered until it is firm, preferrably at least overnight. Garnish the potted kippers with the fresh dill.

Preheat oven to 350 degrees farenheit. Cream sugar and margarine. Add bananas and eggs. Sift cake flour, salt, and baking soda 3 times. Blend flour mixture into banana mixture, making sure not to overmix. Turn out immediately to cool on wire rack.

Preheat oven to 400 degrees. In a large mixing bowl, mash the sweet potatoes. Add the remaining ingredients and blend until smooth and creamy. Spread mixture into a greased 9x9 inch casserole. Bake for 20 minutes or until set. While puff is baking, combine ingredients for topping. After 20 minutes, or once puff has set, spread topping over puff and bake for ten more minutes.

In a large bowl, combine all ingredients. Beat with electric mixer until light and very fluffy. Turn into 1 quart cake dish. Bake at 350 degrees f. In the oven for 20 minutes or until puffed and lightly browned.
Place a layer of white chocolate on top of the white chocolate. Pour over the white chocolate and spread.

Preheat oven to 350 degrees f. Pat pork chops dry with paper towels and generously season with salt and pepper. Heat a large ovenproof skillet over medium high heat. Sear chops in 1 tablespoon of oil until well browned, about 3 to 4 minutes per side. Transfer to a plate. Add remaining tablespoon of oil to skillet and cook onion and rosemary, stirring occasionally, until onions begin to caramelize and turn golden, about 5 minutes. Add garlic and cook another minute. Stir in tomatoes, anchovies, remaining salt and pepper and cook, stirring occasionally, until tomatoes break down, about 8 minutes. Return pork chops to skillet and spoon sauce over chops. Cover skillet and place in preheated oven and cook until internal meat thermometer reads 145 degrees f, about 15 minutes. Serve over polenta, egg noodles, or rice.

In a small mixing bowl, melt butter in microwave. Take breadsticks and cut them in half lengthwise. In a small microwave pyrex bowl, melt butter in microwave. Take each halved breadstick and dip into butter then roll in cinnamon mixture. Twist each strip 2 or 3 times and place on ungreased baking sheets. Bake at 350 degrees for 15 to 18 minutes. Let cool on wire racks. Makes 16 toasted sticks.
Preheat oven to 350 degrees. Bake for about 25-30 minutes or until the cheese is completely melted.

Preheat oven to 350 degrees c. In a small bowl sift together flour and baking soda, set aside. In a large bowl, combine butter and both sugars. Beat on medium speed until light and fluffy, about 3 minutes. Reduce speed to low, add salt, vanilla, and eggs. Beat until just combined. Stir in chocolate chips. Drop heaping spoonfuls about 2 inches apart onto baking trays lined with parchment paper. Bake until golden around the edges and soft in the middle, about 8-10 minutes.

Heat oven to 350 degrees. Cook penne pasta 8 minutes, drain. Mix pasta shell ingredients and toss with pasta. In 9-inch pie plate press pasta to form a shell. Cook ground beef for 4-5 min., breaking into crumbles. Add garlic powder, salt and cumin, stir in tomatoes and cook until almost all liquid has evaporated, stirring occasionally. Remove from heat and add sour cream. Spoon mixture into pasta shell. Add cheese to top and bake 15 minutes.

In large, nonstick skillet, melt butter. Add potatoes and cook over medium heat until tender and lightly browned. Add salt, pepper, and milk, continuing to cook until milk is absorbed and potatoes are tender. Sprinkle with cheese, heating until melted. Stir well, sprinkle with chopped parsley and serve.

Heat oven to 425. Heat margarine in 9 x 13 pan in oven until melted. Mix remaining ingredients except chicken. Coat chicken. Place skin side down in pan. Bake 35 minutes. Turn. Bake until done. About 15 minutes.

Preheat oven to 350 degrees. Place all ingredients into a large mixing bowl and mix until just moistened. Spoon into lined or nonstick, sprayed mini muffin pan. Bake at 350 degrees for 15 minutes. Remove muffins from the tray and cool on a wire rack.
In a large bowl, combine the bananas, oranges, strawberry, seedless grapes, sour cream, honey, orange juice. Add enough dressing to coat and toss well. Sprinkle with almonds and serve.
Preheat oven to 350f. Spray a baking sheet with nonstick spray. Bake for 30 minutes, or until center is set.
Mix together cream cheese, cream cheese, milk, and sugar. Pour into pie crust. Bake at 350 for 45 minutes until set. Serve with ice cream or cool whip.

Preheat oven to 375 degrees f. Place the chicken, with the skins on, in a single layer in a shallow roasting dish and set aside. Heat the oil in a small saucepan and gently fry the green onions and garlic for about 2 minutes, until softened, but not browned. Add the honey, orange juice, orange segments and soy sauce to the pan, stirring well and cook until the honey has completely dissolved. Pour the sauce over the chicken and bake, uncovered, for about 45 minutes, basting once or twice until the chicken is cooked.
Place salmon fillet in foil packet and place horseradish sauce on top. Grill for 8-10 minutes.

On one slice of sourdough bread, layer slice of cheddar cheese, ham, slice of swiss cheese and fried egg. Top with other slice of bread. Brush melted butter on sandwich and place buttered side down in skillet used to fry ham. Brush melted butter on top. Heat dressing in large nonstick skillet on medium heat. Add vegetables. Stir fry for about 8-10 minutes, vegetables should be somewhat cooked but still tender. Add peanut butter and soy sauce. Stir fry 2 minutes or until mixture is heated through. Serve over salad greens.

Combine balsamic vinegar, extra virgin olive oil, balsamic vinegar, dijon mustard, garlic cloves, sugar, fresh lemon, salt, fresh ground pepper. Cook, stirring constantly, until mixture is heated. Serve over balsamic vinaigrette.

Preheat oven to 350. Place the ww in a large bowl and cover with foil. Bake for 15 minutes or until the ww is golden brown.

Bring a large pot of salted water to a boil. Add potatoes and cook until tender but still firm, about 15 minutes. Drain and mash. Melt butter in a large skillet over medium-high heat. Saute tomatoes, onion, chile sauce, green onion, garlic powder, salt and pepper. Stir in potatoes and cook until heated through. Spoon potato mixture into a 2 quart casserole dish and sprinkle with cheese. Serve when the cheese has melted.

Preheat oven to 350 degrees f. In a large bowl, combine the egg, breadcrumbs, parmesan cheese, milk and onion. Remove sausage from casings. Add sausage to the bread crumb mixture and mix well. Shape into 20 meatballs. Arrange meatballs on a shallow baking pan. Bake for 20 minutes or until meatballs are cooked through. Serve with your favorite sauce and spaghetti.

In same pan, melt butter over high heat and saute meat mixture until seared all over. Stir in berbere spice mix to taste. Saute for 30 seconds. Serve with injera bread and tomato & cucumber salad. Keep extra berbere spice mix on table to sprinkle over meat as desired.
Preheat oven to 350f. Mix ingredients together in a large bowl until well-blended. Roll peanut butter mixture into tablespoon size balls. Bake 12 minutes for chewy cookies. Bake 15 minutes for crisp.

Cook the chicken in pan, turning. Cook the chicken until juices are clear when pierced with a fork. Remove the chicken and keep warm. Combine the juices and jelly in the frying pan. Spoon potato mixture into a 2 quart casserole dish and sprinkle with cheese. Serve when the cheese has melted.

Heat oil over medium heat. Saut garlic until soft, being careful not to let it burn. Add sliced mushrooms and saut until beans are just cooked and, of course, no longer frozen. If not on the south beach diet or watching sugar intake, you could add oyster sauce or other asian condiment to the mixture.

Heat wok or deep frying pan over high heat. Add oil, onions, ginger and curry and cook 1 minute. Add stock and coconut milk and bring to simmer. Add the pumpkin, cover and cook for 5 minutes. Add the eggplants and beans and cook another 5 minutes until the pumpkin is soft. Stir in basil. Serve with rice.

Preheat oven to 425. In a saucepan over medium heat, melt the butter. Add flour and stir thoroughly. Add chicken, peas, carrots, onion and salt. Heat to boiling. Pour into a 1. 5 liter casserole. Top with uncooked biscuits. Bake at 425 8-10 minutes or until the biscuits are done.

Briefly heat oil in large pot over medium-high heat. Add beef and onion. Cook, stirring frequently, for 5 minutes. Add garlic, mushrooms and carrots. Cook another 5 minutes. Add pilaf mix, orange juice and beef broth. Bring to a boil, then reduce heat and simmer, covered, for 20 minutes or until liquid has been absorbed.

Preheat oven to 375 degrees. Mix all dry ingredients in large bowl. Combine wet ingredients in a bowl. Mix dry and wet ingredients together. Pour into prepared pancakes and bake at 375 for 20 to 25 minutes.

Place chicken skin side down on middle of grill and turn off inner burners so that heat is indirect. Turn chicken when skin is nicely browned and continue to cook for 1-2 hours or until meat thermometer registers 170 deg f. Remove from heat, cover loosely with foil and let sit for 5 minutes before serving.
Heat olive oil over medium heat. Add quinoa and cook until soft. Add parsley, mint, currants and orange zest. Stir with a fork to combine and fluff up grain.

Place pork tenderloin on a broiler pan and broil until well browned to remove excess fat. Bake at 425 degrees for about 25-35 minutes, or until the thermometer registers 160 degrees. Let stand 5 minutes before slicing. Serve with mango chutney.

Preheat oven to 400 degrees f. Cut vegetables into wedges, like you would steak cut fries. Beat egg with 1 tablespoon water. Mix parmesan cheese with herb seasoning. Dip zucchini into egg, then coat with cheese by pressing slices into mixture. Bake on well greased baking sheet for approximately 15 minutes, or until vegetables reach desired browness. You can also turn them carefully to brown on both sides. I do not turn them when i make them.

Preheat oven to 350 degrees farenheit. Cream sugar and margarine. Add bananas and eggs. Sift cake flour, salt, and baking soda 3 times. Blend flour mixture into cake mixture, making sure not to overmix. Turn batter into 2 greased 9x5x3-inch loaf pans. Bake for 55 minutes, or until toothpick inserted in center of loaf comes out clean. Turn out immediately to cool on wire rack.

In a large heavy pot, saute the clams in butter until transparent. Add flour and blend. Cook for 4-5 minutes but do not brown. Add clams and clam juice. Cook and stir until smooth and comes to a boil. Cook potatoes in a different pot until done. Drain potatoes and add to clam mixture. Adjust seasoning to taste with salt, pepper and worcestershire sauce and blend.

Heat oven to 425. Scrub the potatoes, rinse, and pat dry. Cut each potato length ways into 8 wedges. Put the wedges in a roasting tin, drizzle over the oil and toss well to coat the potatoes. Preheat oven to 350f. Mix all the dry ingredients together. Mix all the wet ingredients together. Mix everything together. Shape into 8-12 balls, put on cooked sheet lined with parchement. Flatten slightly. Leave room between them because the will spread out. Bake for 10-12 minutes at 350f.

Heat oven to 375. Stir together cracker crumbs, flour and baking powder. Set aside. Beat sweetened condensed milk and butter until smooth. Add in dry mixture, mixing well. Stir in chocolates, candy, coconut and pecans. Drop by rounded tbsp onto ungreased cookie sheet. Bake 8-10 minutes or until lightly browned. Cool 1 minute. Remove from cookie sheet to wire racks. Cool completely.

Preheat oven to 350f. Toss together oats, buttermilk, eggs, brown sugar, butter, flour, baking powder, salt, baking soda, raisinspreparation:Fill muffin tins with paper baking cups. Combine oats and buttermilk in a bowl, let stand for 1 hour. Add raisins. Mix on low speed for about 15 seconds or only until dry ingredients are moistened. Fill muffin tins with paper baking cups half full. Bake at 400 degrees for 15-20 minutes.

Preheat oven to 375 degrees. In a small bowl pour stuffing mix and water. Open chicken breasts, and if they are too thick to fold in half flatten and stretch them by placing on cutting board and using heavy rolling pin roll out chicken until it is able to be folded in half. Give the stuffing a quick mix with a spoon. Spoon stuffing onto one half of the chicken and fold chicken breast over to cover. Place breasts in baking pan. Continue stuffing breasts until all breasts are used. If you have left over stuffing go back and open breasts and continue stuffing until all stuffing is used. Combine soup and sour cream. Spread over chicken breasts. Cover and bake for 45 minutes to an hour until chicken is thoroughly cooked.

In 3-quart saucepan, cover potatoes with water. Bring to a boil. Reduce heat to low and simmer 20 minutes or until potatoes are very tender. Drain. Return potatoes to saucepan. Mash. Stir in remaining ingredients.

In a saucepan, bring 2 inches of water to a boil. Add peppers and tomatoes and cook for 5 minutes, or until tomatoes are tender. Place peppers and tomatoes in colander, pour in cooked peppers and hot water to drain. In skillet over high heat, cook garlic in olive oil 1 minute. Add garlic and onion and cook on a low slow heat until the onions are transparent. Add chillies to the garlic and onion mixture and cook until the chillies are soft. Again being careful not to brown or burn the garlic, onion and chilli mixture. Next, to the mixture in the saucepan, add the tamarind paste, fish sauce and the sugar. Simmer for ten minutes then turn off heat. Cool for a few minutes and then pour the mixture into a blender or food processor and blend until the mixture is the consistency of jam. Pour into sterilised jam jar and store in fridge. The chilli jam will last for a couple of weeks in the fridge.

Place eggs in a single layer in a large pot. Put just enough cold water in the pot to cover the eggs. Bring to a rapid boil. Remove from burner and cover and let sit in hot water for 20 minutes. Drain eggs and remove shell under cold water. Cut the boiled egg in half lengthwise and remove the yolks and place yolks in a mixing bowl. Reserve your egg halves on an egg tray or platter. Combine all ingredients except dill relish with an electric mixer, blender or processor. Stir in the relish. Either spoon the mixture into the egg whites or pipe it in using a pastry bag or place in a ziploc baggie and snip a corner and squeeze into egg white. Garnish with paprika, parsley or anything else you like.

Bake for 60 minutes or until wooden pick inserted in center comes out clean cool completely in pan. Drizzle with glaze or wait until the cake is sliced and then drizzle with glaze to maximize the glazed area.

Preheat oven to 350f degrees. Layer the first 4 ingredients in a large casserole. Lightly mix. Spread mashed potatoes evenly over the top. Sprinkle the cheese evenly over and sprinkle the pepper over the cheese. Bake on middle oven rack for approximately 45 minutes or until hot and bubbly. Alternately place in 4 to 6 small single serving casseroles. Either way these casseroles freeze well.

Preheat oven to 350f. Add 1/2 cup of water to the casserole dish, cover, reduce heat, and simmer for 5 minutes. Remove from heat, but do not peek. Set aside for at least 5 more minutes to rest. While the rice is resting, saute the onions and mushrooms in the olive oil and butter. When the onions are transparent, remove from the heat, add the finished rice to the saute pan, add salt and pepper and stir.
Preheat oven to 350 degrees. Mix ingredients together in a large bowl until well-blended. Roll quinoa mixture into tablespoon size balls. Bake 12 minutes for chewy cookies. Bake 15 minutes for crisp.

Preheat oven to 450. When oven is ready, warm 2 tbsp of the olive oil in a 9 x 13 inch baking pan. Add rosemary, return to oven until rosemary begins to sizzle. Add shrimp, sprinkle with the orange juice, orange zest, salt and pepper and remaining olive oil. Roast until the shrimp turns pink, about 10 minutes.

Heat oil in 2-quart saucepan. Add onion and garlic. Cook over medium heat for about 5 minutes, until onion wilts. Stir in cumin and pepper. Continue to cook for 2-3 minutes. Add oregano, potatoes, green chilies and chicken broth. Bring to a boil and simmer slowly for 45 minutes. Serve hot with cheese sprinkled in the middle of bowl.

Preheat oven to 350f. Season chicken breasts with garlic powder, salt and pepper. Wrap each chicken breast in 1 strip of bacon and place in a 9x13x2-inch baking dish. In a small bowl, mix the sour cream and soup. Spoon mixture over the chicken and bake uncovered for 40 to 50 minutes or until slightly brown on top. Serve immediately in tacos or use as a filling for enchiladas. Use two forks to shred the chicken into chunks. Add cheese and stir. You can also use chicken breasts, but it turns out drier and not as tasty.

Combine the sour cream, mayonnaise and salad dressing and mix well. Squeeze the spinach to remove water. Add to the mixture and mix well. Add optional ingredient. Hollow out the bread that was removed from the loaves. Arrange assorted cut up veggies and bread cubes around loaves.
Lay graham crackers in a single layer on a cookie sheet. Boil oleo and brown sugar 4 minutes. Pour over graham crackers. Sprinkle top with nuts. Bake at 350 for 6-8 minutes.

In a large skillet, heat oil to medium-high heat. Add chicken and brown. Put chicken in crockpot. Add frozen vegetables and tapioca. Mix well. In a small bowl, mix all remaining ingredients. Pour on the chicken. Cover and bake at low heat for 4 hours.

Place meatballs in a crockpot. Add the meatballs to crockpot and heat on low. May be served over rice, noodles, or potatoes.

Add water to a saucepan. Bring to a boil. Stir in the oats, raisins, apricots, figs, sugar, vanilla, cinnamon, cardamom, salt. Lower heat to med-low. Simmer, uncovered, for about 5-10 minutes or until the liquid is absorbed and the fruit softened.

Preheat oven to 350f. Cream together margarine, white sugar, baking soda, vanilla, eggs, instant vanilla pudding, flour, milk chocolate chips. Add in all the chocolate and mix. Bake at 350 for 15-18 minutes or until golden brown.

Melt butter in medium saucepan on medium-high heat. Add onions. Cook 3 to 5 minutes or until crisp-tender, stirring frequently. Whisk in flour until blended. Add broth and milk. Cook on medium-high heat 2 minutes or until heated through, stirring frequently. Add salt& pepper to taste and garnish with kluski noodles.

Preheat oven to 350f. Mix all the dry ingredients together. Mix all the wet ingredients together. Mix everything together. Shape into 8-12 balls, put on cooked sheet lined with parchement. Flatten slightly. Leave room between them because the will spread out. Bake for 10-12 minutes at 350f.

Heat grill to medium-high heat. Mix mayo and basil. Refrigerate until ready to use. Combine meat and garlic. Shape into 8 thin patties. Top 4 patties with cheese. Cover with remaining patties. Pinch edges together to seal. Grill 7 to 9 minute on each side or until burgers are done. Spread buns with mayo mixture. Fill with lettuce, tomatoes, burgers and peppers.

Remove from heat, drain, and puree in a food processor. In a large bowl, whisk together flour, baking powder, sugar, salt and pumpkin pie spice. In a medium bowl, thoroughly mix together milk, egg and applesauce. Stir in squash. Fold the squash mixture into the flour mixture just until moistened. Spoon batter into the greased muffin pan, filling cups about full. Bake 20 minutes.

In small bowl, pour 1 cup boiling water over tomatoes. Let stand at room temperature 5-10 minutes. Drain and chop tomatoes. Meanwhile, in another small bowl, combine cream cheese, yogurt and chili sauce. Mix well. Add tomatoes and all remaining ingredients. Refrigerate till serving time. Just before serving. Stir dip. Serve with cut up fresh veggies or garlic flavored bagel crisps.

Combine pepper cream cheese and jalapenos in a small bowl. Mix well. Add the jalapenos. Serve with chips, pita or vegetables.
Chop the carrot and apple. Add all ingredients to the blender and puree. Add more liquid if needed. Adjust taste to your liking. Store in the fridge until ready to serve or serve right away.

Melt chocolate in large non-stick pan over medium-low heat. Add marshmallows and stir until melted and smooth. Turn off flame. Stir in chocolate chips and continue folding until well coated. Spray 13 x 9 pan with cooking spray and press mixture into pan. Cool and cut into squares.

Combine radishes, goat cheese, baguette, coarse salt and pepper in a large mixing bowl and mix well. Add the radishes and mix well. Cover and refrigerate for 30 minutes or overnight. Serve warm.

Preheat oven to 375 degrees. Mix all dry ingredients in large bowl. Combine wet ingredients in a bowl. Mix dry and wet ingredients together. Pour into prepared muffin pans and bake at 375 for 20 to 25 minutes.

Heat oil over medium heat. Saut garlic until soft, being careful not to let it burn. Add sliced mushrooms and saut until they look fairly cooked and shiny. If not on the south beach diet or watching sugar intake, you could add oyster sauce or other asian condiment to the mixture.

Heat oven to 350 degrees. Cook quesadilla for 4-5 min., breaking into crumbles. Add garlic powder, salt and cumin, stir in tomatoes and cook until almost all liquid has evaporated, stirring occasionally. Remove from heat and add sour cream. Spoon mixture into pasta shell. Add cheese to top and bake 15 minutes.

Place tea bags in a large heat-proof measuring cup or pitcher. Pour boiling water over tea bags. Steep 1 hour, or until cooled to room temperature. Remove and discard tea bags. Add pomegranate juice and splenda, stirring until it dissolves. Serve over ice. Garnish with mint sprigs. Makes 4, 1 cup servings.

Heat salted water in a large saucepan until boiling. Cook the beans until tender, about 7 minutes. Drain beans. Set aside to cool. Whisk together the garlic, vinegar, mustard, salt and pepper to taste in a small bowl. Slowly whisk in the olive oil, adding in a steady stream, until smooth. Combine the reserved beans, green onions, mushrooms and parsley in a large bowl. Pour dressing over vegetables. Toss lightly. Chill 30 minutes before serving.
Place beef chuck roast in crock pot. Cover and cook on low for 1 hour. Slice and serve.

Preheat oven to 350f. Toss together apples, sugar, flour, cinnamon and oats. Using pastry cutter work butter into oat mixture until crumbly. Spread over fruit, pressing down lightly. Potatoes will be done when slightly browned and fork-tender.

Mix together milk, honey, lemon rind, ground cinnamon, bread, eggs, vegetable oil, sour cream, clear honey, lemon wedge. Bake 20 minutes edges may start to brown a little.

Remove the hot pot from the oven. Uncover and brush the potatoes again with melted butter or dripping. Return to the oven for a further 30 minutes, uncovered, to brown the potatoes. Preheat oven to 325f. Combine cream cheese, sugar and eggs in a small bowl. Beat until fluffy. Place crust on baking sheet. Pour mixture into crust. Bake 25 to 30 minutes. Remove from oven. Cool. Spread chocolate filling on top. Garnish with whipped topping. Chill 3 hours.

In medium size sauce pan over medium-high heat combine soy milk with sugar, vanilla, and cinnamon bring to a boil while constantly stirring. In a separate bowl large enough to accommodate the hot liquid beat the egg with a whisk while slowly adding the hot liquid a little bit at a time until all of the liquid has been added to the egg. Place the 2 cups of cooked rice into the pan used to cook the soy milk mixture. Add the soy milk mixture to the rice in the pan and return heat to medium-high, stir constantly until the mixture comes to a boil then reduce heat to simmer. Simmer mixture for 15-20 minutes, stirring every 5 minutes until the mixture is a creamy consistency. Remove from heat, cover top with wax paper and place in the refrigerator to cool.

Preheat oven to 350 degrees f. For the filling, beat cream cheese on medium speed until fluffy. Beat in sugar until blended, then beat in eggs until blended. Stir in white chocolate, cranberries, zest & vanilla. Pour into prepared crust & bake 45-50 minutes or until center is almost set. Cool in pan for 30 minutes, then refrigerate. Run knife around sides of pan to loosen, then chill 4 hours or more. Remove rim & cut into wedges. Refrigerate leftovers.
